(TIRES SCREECHING)

01:07.225 --> 01:09.027
(CAR DOOR CLOSES)

01:21.638 --> 01:23.808
Can I get a pack of Morleys?

01:26.644 --> 01:29.178
<i>¿Cigarillos? ¿Comprende?</i>

01:29.180 --> 01:30.815
<i>Sí, sí.</i>

01:34.618 --> 01:36.754
(PHONE RINGING)

01:38.722 --> 01:40.223
(CLERK SPEAKS SPANISH)

01:40.225 --> 01:43.024
Yeah.

01:43.026 --> 01:45.564
(CLERK SPEAKING SPANISH)

01:53.204 --> 01:55.505
(DEMONIC VOICE):
Truth or dare, Giselle?

01:55.507 --> 01:56.905
(CRYING):
Please.

01:56.907 --> 01:59.041
Please, I don't want
to play anymore. Please.

01:59.043 --> 02:02.612
- Truth... or... dare?
- (GISELLE GASPS)

02:02.614 --> 02:04.549
♪ ♪

02:11.155 --> 02:12.491
(GASPS)

02:13.090 --> 02:14.824
Oh, no! No!

02:14.826 --> 02:16.528
I'm sorry.
I don't have a choice.

02:17.794 --> 02:20.499
(WOMAN SCREAMING)

02:24.736 --> 02:27.206
(SCREAMING CONTINUES)

02:30.107 --> 02:32.107
OLIVIA:
<i>You do have a choice.</i>

02:32.109 --> 02:34.809
And I can honestly say
the pure joy you will feel

02:34.811 --> 02:36.312
from literally building
someone's home,

02:36.314 --> 02:39.181
it will stay with you
for the rest of your life.

02:39.183 --> 02:41.183
Unlike all the nights
you won't remember

02:41.185 --> 02:44.119
and the hangovers you're
really gonna want to forget.

02:44.121 --> 02:46.154
So, for a spring break
alternative

02:46.156 --> 02:48.089
that is really good
for the soul,

02:48.091 --> 02:51.627
please consider
Habitat for Humanity.

02:51.629 --> 02:52.895
Okay.

02:52.897 --> 02:54.897
Hey.

02:54.899 --> 02:56.798
Hi.

02:56.800 --> 03:00.169
So, I've been doing some
thinking, and I forgive you.

03:00.171 --> 03:02.872
- For what?
- For saying you can't come on spring break.

03:02.874 --> 03:05.206
I know you didn't mean it.

03:05.208 --> 03:07.009
- Markie.
- Yeah?

03:07.011 --> 03:09.744
I love you so much,
you know that.

03:09.746 --> 03:11.647
But I can't. I already
signed up for Habitat.

03:11.649 --> 03:13.315
- I know.
- Yeah. I'm a trip leader.

03:13.317 --> 03:16.685
You know what, I know, I know.
It's just...

03:16.687 --> 03:20.755
this is our last
spring break, ever.

03:20.757 --> 03:23.825
And the thought of doing that
without my best friend...

03:23.827 --> 03:25.327
that breaks my heart.

03:25.329 --> 03:27.997
Since high school, you and I
haven't spent more than a week

03:27.999 --> 03:29.198
away from each other.

03:29.200 --> 03:31.734
This is our last chance
to have some fun

03:31.736 --> 03:34.236
before life tears us apart.

03:34.238 --> 03:37.139
I mean, when you
put it that way...

03:37.141 --> 03:39.742
- Yeah.
- No. Still can't.

03:39.744 --> 03:42.310
Okay. Olivia,
what ever happened to

03:42.312 --> 03:44.046
"between you and the world,
I choose you"?

03:44.048 --> 03:45.280
- I still mean that.
- Do you?

03:45.282 --> 03:47.349
Yes, most of the time.
This just...

03:47.351 --> 03:49.684
you know, isn't
one of those times.

03:49.686 --> 03:51.386
Okay. All right.
You know, I really didn't want

03:51.388 --> 03:53.990
to have to do this, but
you've left me no other choice.

03:53.992 --> 03:55.190
I un-signed you up.

03:55.192 --> 03:57.892
- You what?
- Yeah.

03:57.894 --> 03:59.729
I told Habitat
you got shingles.

03:59.731 --> 04:02.030
Which is kind of funny,
'cause roofs have shingles...

04:02.032 --> 04:03.231
Markie, that is so...

04:03.233 --> 04:05.735
- Brilliant.
- Thank you.

04:05.737 --> 04:07.937
Okay, if you come with us
for this one week

04:07.939 --> 04:11.407
of spring break debauchery, we
will all build houses with you

04:11.409 --> 04:12.908
for two weeks over the summer.

04:12.910 --> 04:14.343
- We said one week.
- We said two.

04:14.345 --> 04:15.810
It'll help with your
med school applications.

04:15.812 --> 04:17.077
- Like I need the help.
- He's in.

04:17.079 --> 04:18.346
Full 14 days.

04:18.349 --> 04:19.346
MARKIE:
So what's it gonna be, Liv?

04:19.349 --> 04:21.817
I mean, your feeble set
of hands for one week,

04:21.819 --> 04:23.753
or all of ours for two?

04:23.755 --> 04:25.121
I mean, you're really
just being selfish

04:25.123 --> 04:27.156
if you don't come with us.

04:27.158 --> 04:29.190
(SIGHS)

04:29.192 --> 04:31.163
♪ ♪

04:34.332 --> 04:35.798
- Oh, my God.
- (TYSON GROANS)

04:35.800 --> 04:37.233
- (LAUGHS)
- What did you put in here?

04:37.235 --> 04:38.767
Shoes.

04:38.769 --> 04:40.902
- It worked?
- OLIVIA: Well, that depends.

04:40.904 --> 04:42.904
Are you really gonna help me
build houses this summer?

04:42.906 --> 04:44.739
You had me at
"boys with tools."

04:44.741 --> 04:47.008
And Markie's nothing
if not persistent.

04:47.010 --> 04:50.047
Yep, that is
her most annoying quality.

04:53.017 --> 04:55.084
Glad you're with us,
Girl Scout.

04:55.086 --> 04:57.019
Well, you know we've always
been a package deal.

04:57.021 --> 04:59.854
Oh, yeah.
I'm well aware of that.

04:59.856 --> 05:01.890
- Are you?
- Yeah. I'm okay with it.

05:01.892 --> 05:03.392
LUCAS:
Mm.

05:03.394 --> 05:05.260
- You ready?
- So ready.

05:05.262 --> 05:07.697
- Okay, let's go.
- Let's do it.

05:07.699 --> 05:08.830
(LUCAS SIGHS)

05:08.832 --> 05:10.933
- Do we have everything?
- Yeah.

05:10.935 --> 05:12.868
Now we do.

05:12.870 --> 05:15.104
- Ow, ow! Spring break, bitches!
- (ENGINE STARTS)

05:15.106 --> 05:18.808
- (WHOOPING, LAUGHING)
- LUCAS: That's right, bitches!

05:18.810 --> 05:22.346
("NO VOY A REGRESAR"
BY CECI BASTIDA PLAYING)

05:25.882 --> 05:28.851
- (SHOUTING, WHOOPING)
- (CAMERA CLICKS)

05:28.853 --> 05:31.820
BRAD:
<i>¡Viva la Mexico!</i>

05:31.822 --> 05:33.789
LUCAS:
<i>There it is!</i>

05:33.791 --> 05:35.724
<i>We're in Mexico.</i>

05:35.726 --> 05:38.493
- Yay! - Rosarito! Spring break!
- Spring break!

05:38.495 --> 05:41.397
Who's ready for some cervezas?

05:41.399 --> 05:44.299
- Margaritas. - Actually, this
is, like, our fourth. - (GROANS)

05:44.301 --> 05:45.500
I love you.

05:45.502 --> 05:47.335
- I love you.
- LUCAS: <i>Such a babe.</i>

05:47.337 --> 05:50.339
- <i>My God.</i>
- OLIVIA: <i>What about me?</i>

05:50.341 --> 05:51.873
<i>Mexico!</i>

05:51.875 --> 05:53.976
Tyson... is about to run
into the water

05:53.978 --> 05:55.844
and get eaten by a shark.

05:55.846 --> 05:58.113
- PENELOPE: <i>Spring break!</i>
- LUCAS: <i>Beer run. Let's go!</i>

05:58.115 --> 06:01.082
- We're not drunk yet.
- (SINGING)

06:01.084 --> 06:02.851
Are you straight? Are you
straight? Are you straight?

06:02.853 --> 06:04.253
All poles, no holes.

06:04.255 --> 06:05.854
You know that.

06:05.856 --> 06:09.125
- <i>Get a room.</i>
- Lonely souls here at the bar.

06:09.127 --> 06:10.859
- Drink. Drink.
- MARKIE: <i>Oh.</i>

06:10.861 --> 06:13.361
Sand dollar!
Lucky charm.

06:13.363 --> 06:16.332
- Sober friend right here.
- Huh? Not!

06:16.334 --> 06:19.301
♪ ♪

06:19.303 --> 06:21.503
(GROWLING)

06:21.505 --> 06:24.472
There, there. Yeah!
(LAUGHS): Oh, shit! Oh, my...

06:24.474 --> 06:27.041
- (LAUGHING) - MARKIE: <i>I love it.</i>
- LUCAS: <i>Nice!</i>

06:27.043 --> 06:28.145
(CAMERA CLICKING RAPIDLY)

06:29.312 --> 06:31.147
Mwah! Whoo!

06:31.149 --> 06:32.481
If you guys watch this later,

06:32.483 --> 06:33.983
- I love you, Markie.
- Soul brothers. (GROWLS)

06:33.985 --> 06:35.818
Love you, Liv.

06:35.820 --> 06:38.486
- Love you, Pen. Love you, Brad. I love you, Ty.
- Yes, we are...

06:38.488 --> 06:41.457
Let's leave these losers
behind. Let's go.

06:41.459 --> 06:42.957
No, I just want to go
to one more bar.

06:42.959 --> 06:44.960
- <i>¡Olé!</i>
- <i>¡Olé!</i>

06:44.962 --> 06:46.227
Oh, I want to lay you.

06:46.229 --> 06:47.897
Let's go back to the hotel.
Come on.

06:47.899 --> 06:49.334
(PENELOPE LAUGHS)

06:50.901 --> 06:53.204
♪ ♪

06:58.276 --> 06:59.974
MAN:
<i>¡Uno! ¡Dos!</i>

06:59.976 --> 07:01.844
<i>¡Uno, dos, tres, cuatro!</i>

07:01.846 --> 07:03.415
- (LIVELY DANCE MUSIC PLAYING)
- (CROWD CHEERING)

07:11.955 --> 07:13.455
(CHUCKLES):
Wow.

07:13.457 --> 07:15.293
They are really going for it.

07:16.324 --> 07:19.094
Well, if you can't beat 'em...

07:19.096 --> 07:21.897
- Oh-hoo-hoo. - Mm-hmm.
- Just like that?

07:21.899 --> 07:23.834
♪ ♪

07:31.541 --> 07:35.344
Okay. Tell me what's going on.

07:35.346 --> 07:39.147
Uh, last night
in Mexico, and...

07:39.149 --> 07:41.450
and we're the only two losers
not dancing.

07:41.452 --> 07:44.019
Mm. If you can
call that dancing.

07:44.021 --> 07:45.957
Definitely not.

07:50.127 --> 07:52.361
Is that for your
YouTube channel?

07:52.363 --> 07:54.096
No. No.

07:54.098 --> 07:56.097
YouTube's for
my volunteer stuff,

07:56.099 --> 07:58.234
and Snapchats are just for fun.

07:58.236 --> 08:00.402
Um, I'm gonna go
to the señoritas'.

08:00.404 --> 08:03.037
- I'll be right back.
- Okay. (CLEARS THROAT)

08:03.039 --> 08:05.039
Come on, come on.

08:05.041 --> 08:07.476
Hey, I thought you were
done with this shit.

08:07.478 --> 08:10.145
- You're moving in with Lucas, to D.C., remember?
- Yeah. Yeah.

08:10.147 --> 08:13.315
- What... what are you doing?
- I'm-I'm sorry.

08:13.317 --> 08:15.250
I'm so stupid. I'm just...
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

08:15.252 --> 08:17.519
I'm just drunk, okay?

08:17.521 --> 08:19.858
You're seriously
the best friend ever.

08:21.024 --> 08:22.157
Okay. (SNIFFLES)

08:22.159 --> 08:23.125
- You're good?
- Yeah.

08:23.127 --> 08:27.462
Look who I found
trying and failing to salsa.

08:27.464 --> 08:28.664
LUCAS:
Cool.

08:28.666 --> 08:30.465
- I wasn't that bad.
- Hey.

08:30.467 --> 08:31.600
- Hey.
- I missed you.

08:31.602 --> 08:33.534
- I missed you.
- Welcome back.

08:33.535 --> 08:34.770
MARKIE:
I missed you, too.

08:34.772 --> 08:36.572
LUCAS: So you weren't doing
too well with the salsa, huh?

08:36.573 --> 08:39.408
♪ ♪

08:39.409 --> 08:40.643
(LUCAS LAUGHS)

08:40.645 --> 08:42.347
(OLIVIA SIGHS)

08:43.613 --> 08:47.149
- Olivia! What?
- Ronnie?

08:47.151 --> 08:49.250
Hi. What are you doing here?

08:49.252 --> 08:51.419
Oh, I'm just skiing. What
do you think I'm doing here?

08:51.421 --> 08:54.289
I'm getting my spring break on.
Do you want to join me?

08:54.291 --> 08:56.158
(CHUCKLES)
No. Thanks.

08:56.160 --> 08:58.159
Hey, where's Markie?
Maybe we could do, like,

08:58.161 --> 09:00.228
- you know, a little ménage à trois?
- You know what?

09:00.230 --> 09:01.996
She's actually
with her boyfriend, Lucas.

09:01.998 --> 09:03.531
What about, like,
a ménage à dos?

09:03.533 --> 09:06.003
CARTER:
Not happening, pal.

09:07.504 --> 09:10.039
Oh, yeah?
Is there a problem, pal?

09:10.041 --> 09:12.274
No.

09:12.276 --> 09:14.543
I'm just surprised she hasn't
punched you in the face yet.

09:14.545 --> 09:16.946
- Guess she's nicer than I am.
- Oh, yeah?

09:16.948 --> 09:18.579
How about I punch you
in the face? Huh?

09:18.581 --> 09:19.615
Wouldn't be the worst thing

09:19.617 --> 09:20.949
that's happened to me
this week.

09:20.951 --> 09:21.983
Okay, Ronnie, calm down.

09:21.985 --> 09:24.319
Seriously, you got to
let it go.

09:24.321 --> 09:27.021
All right? I saw Delta Phi in
the back. They're doing shots.

09:27.023 --> 09:29.193
So you should
really go check it out.

09:31.094 --> 09:33.227
I can't say no to shots.
Everyone knows that.

09:33.229 --> 09:35.499
That's why I'm gonna leave,
not 'cause of what you said.

09:38.401 --> 09:40.037
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

09:41.973 --> 09:43.639
You think I'm too nice?

09:43.641 --> 09:45.207
It's a good thing.

09:45.209 --> 09:47.208
Except when dealing
with guys at bars, so...

09:47.210 --> 09:49.178
Feel free to tell me
to piss off.

09:49.180 --> 09:52.117
Maybe I just like being nice.

09:54.017 --> 09:56.050
Can I give it a shot?

09:56.052 --> 09:58.419
(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

09:58.421 --> 10:00.356
- I'm Carter.
- Olivia.

10:00.358 --> 10:01.756
Buy you a drink?

10:01.758 --> 10:03.358
Yeah.

10:03.360 --> 10:04.994
Another beer,

10:04.996 --> 10:08.130
and... a margarita
for the lady.

10:08.132 --> 10:10.064
(PEOPLE CHATTERING IN SPANISH)

10:10.066 --> 10:12.067
(MARIACHI MUSIC PLAYING
IN DISTANCE)

10:12.069 --> 10:14.035
Come on!

10:14.037 --> 10:15.571
There's got to be an all-night
bar around here somewhere.

10:15.573 --> 10:17.573
We still have that tequila
back in the room.

10:17.575 --> 10:18.673
But it's our last night
in Mexico.

10:18.675 --> 10:20.742
I don't want
to go back to the room.

10:20.744 --> 10:22.711
I know a place we can go.

10:22.713 --> 10:26.180
- I'm... I'm sorry, who are you?
- (CHUCKLES)

10:26.182 --> 10:29.451
- Uh, it's a bit of a hike, but it's worth it.
- Hmm.

10:29.453 --> 10:32.187
Or you can just tell me
to piss off.

10:32.189 --> 10:33.654
MARKIE:
I think, uh...

10:33.656 --> 10:36.091
think the hotel room
sounds pretty good, yeah.

10:36.093 --> 10:38.530
- BRAD: Yeah.
- Oh, come on, it's our final spring break.

10:40.397 --> 10:44.566
Before life tears us apart.

10:44.568 --> 10:46.404
Right.

10:48.305 --> 10:49.638
♪ ♪

10:49.640 --> 10:51.576
CARTER:
We're almost there.

10:54.310 --> 10:56.311
BRAD: I should have worn
my hiking shoes.

10:56.313 --> 10:57.645
MARKIE:
Um... okay.

10:57.647 --> 10:59.615
BRAD: Should I lay down
some bread crumbs?

10:59.617 --> 11:01.019
OLIVIA:
Wait, guys, be careful.

11:02.652 --> 11:05.289
Wonder what that means.
How's your Spanish, Brad? Ow.

11:09.259 --> 11:11.428
Come on, guys, let's go.

11:15.366 --> 11:18.699
(DOOR CREAKING)

11:18.701 --> 11:21.636
Wow. This place is interesting.

11:21.638 --> 11:23.204
(CHUCKLES)

11:23.206 --> 11:25.106
- Kind of terrifying.
- Uh...

11:25.108 --> 11:26.741
There's nothing
to be afraid of.

11:26.743 --> 11:28.309
Promise.

11:28.311 --> 11:30.578
BRAD: Uh, yeah, this is
way better than a club.

11:30.580 --> 11:32.713
Hey. You okay?

11:32.715 --> 11:35.116
Uh, yeah. Yeah.

11:35.118 --> 11:38.287
- Just a little tired.
- Yeah. We won't stay long.

11:38.289 --> 11:40.492
PENELOPE:
Where's the tequila?

11:44.094 --> 11:46.260
Hope you've had
your tetanus shot.

11:46.262 --> 11:48.130
I got to piss.

11:48.132 --> 11:50.101
(POP SONG PLAYING QUIETLY)

11:52.335 --> 11:54.705
- Nice. Thank you.
- Cool, cool. Thanks, man.

12:17.728 --> 12:19.763
♪ ♪

12:35.345 --> 12:38.347
- Oh!
- (FLIES BUZZING)

12:38.349 --> 12:39.783
Ugh.

12:42.219 --> 12:44.155
♪ ♪

12:53.497 --> 12:56.198
- (GASPS)
- Oh! Yo! Chill out, O-dog, it's just me.

12:56.200 --> 12:58.500
Ronnie, did you follow me here?

12:58.502 --> 13:00.736
You can't keep Ron-Ron
from a party.

13:00.738 --> 13:02.272
(SIGHS)

13:03.339 --> 13:05.506
What the hell?
(SNIFFS)

13:05.508 --> 13:07.544
This smells horrible.
What is... what...

13:13.684 --> 13:15.851
(POP SONG PLAYING QUIETLY)

13:15.853 --> 13:17.752
RONNIE:
Yo, beer me, bro.

13:17.754 --> 13:20.588
Oh, great, Ronnie's here.

13:20.590 --> 13:22.823
Sure thing, bro.

13:22.825 --> 13:25.327
Um, you know, we got to

13:25.329 --> 13:27.261
- get up early, so...
- Yeah. - Yeah. - Yes.

13:27.263 --> 13:29.798
- Yeah, yeah.
- CARTER: You guys just got here.

13:29.800 --> 13:32.733
- You can't leave now.
- Yeah. What's the rush?

13:32.735 --> 13:34.702
Um...

13:34.704 --> 13:36.538
Yeah, let's, uh, let's play
a game or something.

13:36.540 --> 13:38.506
Oh, yeah, like spin the bottle.

13:38.508 --> 13:41.610
- And on that note, let's, uh...
- I was thinking Truth or Dare.

13:41.612 --> 13:44.746
What, this a seventh grade
sleepover, or...?

13:44.748 --> 13:47.783
I know it's a kids' game, but,
I mean, if you play it right,

13:47.785 --> 13:50.952
it's a chance to expose
your friends' deepest secrets,

13:50.954 --> 13:54.325
and... make them do
things they don't want to.

13:55.993 --> 13:58.327
That actually does sound
kind of interesting.

13:58.329 --> 13:59.995
Uh...

13:59.997 --> 14:01.597
Great. We're in.

14:01.599 --> 14:02.898
Okay, everybody, get behind me.

14:02.900 --> 14:05.667
- And... one, two, three.
- Smile. - <i>Queso.</i>

14:05.669 --> 14:08.937
- Yo, will you tag me in that? Your boy.
- (BRAD GROANS)

14:08.939 --> 14:11.005
Glad you're with us, Ronnie.

14:11.007 --> 14:14.610
(CHUCKLING, GROANING)

14:14.612 --> 14:16.912
(SIGHS)
Well?

14:16.914 --> 14:18.614
Olivia, truth or dare?

14:18.616 --> 14:20.749
- MARKIE: Whoo!
- Hmm.

14:20.751 --> 14:22.918
- Truth.
- Lame.

14:22.920 --> 14:26.487
Um... aliens.

14:26.489 --> 14:28.457
They land right now
and they give you a choice.

14:28.459 --> 14:31.360
They kill everyone
in this room,

14:31.362 --> 14:33.629
and then leave
peacefully, or...

14:33.631 --> 14:36.731
they kill the entire
population of Mexico,

14:36.733 --> 14:39.268
but we escape unscathed.

14:39.270 --> 14:40.702
Choose.

14:40.704 --> 14:42.504
What kind of ridiculous
question is that?

14:42.506 --> 14:45.274
- It's a moral dilemma.
- I don't have morals.

14:45.276 --> 14:46.842
- Of course you don't.
- Okay, well, obviously,

14:46.844 --> 14:49.443
- she's choosing us.
- Sorry, guys.

14:49.445 --> 14:52.547
- What?
- (GASPS) You're gonna let aliens kill us?

14:52.549 --> 14:54.683
I love you, but millions
of people? Come on.

14:54.685 --> 14:56.550
You have to tell the truth.

