of showing you my business.

30:29.419 --> 30:31.588
- Gross.
- Ugh.

30:33.389 --> 30:35.255
- (NECK CRACKS)
- (OLIVIA GASPS)

30:35.257 --> 30:37.291
(PEOPLE GASPING, SCREAMING)

30:37.293 --> 30:39.293
MAN:
Call 911!

30:39.295 --> 30:41.861
Bad break.

30:41.863 --> 30:44.634
- It's a pool joke.
- That's not funny.

30:46.568 --> 30:49.603
- It's the game.
- What?

30:49.605 --> 30:51.805
- It is. It followed us home.
- Are-are you being serious?

30:51.807 --> 30:53.841
Carter told me
that it was real,

30:53.843 --> 30:55.610
that we were all in,
and that it would find us.

30:55.612 --> 30:56.944
TYSON:
We're really taking the word

30:56.946 --> 30:58.778
of our mentally unstable
tour guide?

30:58.780 --> 31:01.248
How else do you explain what
happened to me in the library?

31:01.250 --> 31:03.251
- Huh? And now Ronnie?
- Oh, I don't know.

31:03.253 --> 31:04.919
Maybe he was drunk
and he fell off a pool table,

31:04.921 --> 31:06.621
- which is what happened.
- So, it's just a coincidence that

31:06.623 --> 31:08.688
- he was supposed to be doing a dare?
- Let's just calm down.

31:08.690 --> 31:11.292
- Yes.
- No. Carter said, "Tell the truth or you die.

31:11.294 --> 31:13.828
Do the dare or you die."
Ronnie chickened out.

31:13.830 --> 31:15.963
He did not do his dare,
and now he's dead!

31:15.965 --> 31:19.300
Guys, tell me I'm not crazy!

31:19.302 --> 31:21.669
LUCAS: Oh, no,
you definitely sound crazy.

31:21.671 --> 31:23.504
OLIVIA:
Lucas.

31:23.506 --> 31:25.505
(PANTING) I am so sorry

31:25.507 --> 31:27.475
for what I said,
but I swear to you,

31:27.477 --> 31:29.476
something forced me
to say that.

31:29.478 --> 31:32.280
And I need you to believe me.

31:32.282 --> 31:34.482
Please.

31:34.484 --> 31:36.516
Kind of hard
to believe someone

31:36.518 --> 31:38.622
who's been lying to you
for so long.

31:44.727 --> 31:46.662
See you, guys.

31:50.400 --> 31:53.400
RONNIE (OVER VIDEO): Anyway,
now I will do you all the honor

31:53.402 --> 31:55.338
of showing you my business.

32:02.511 --> 32:04.512
(DEMONIC VOICE):
Lucas.

32:04.514 --> 32:06.950
(MUSIC PLAYING FAINTLY
OVER EARPHONES)

32:23.966 --> 32:26.436
(DEMONIC VOICE):
Lucas.

32:28.970 --> 32:30.906
♪ ♪

32:45.654 --> 32:47.356
(SIGHS)

32:56.132 --> 32:58.698
(DEMONIC VOICE):
Lucas.

32:58.700 --> 33:02.471
(DISTORTED, ECHOING LAUGHTER)

33:04.006 --> 33:06.310
That's very funny, guys.

33:11.546 --> 33:13.848
Okay, this is insane.

33:13.850 --> 33:15.519
(SIGHS)

33:18.921 --> 33:20.787
(GRUNTS)

33:20.789 --> 33:22.590
(QUIET SIZZLING)

33:22.592 --> 33:24.995
(GRUNTING, YELLING)

33:26.863 --> 33:28.498
(PANICKED GASPING)

33:30.932 --> 33:33.033
(SCREAMING)

33:33.035 --> 33:34.970
(PHONE BUZZING)

33:39.007 --> 33:40.844
Hey.

33:41.943 --> 33:43.878
I believe you.

33:43.880 --> 33:46.913
Something started burning
"truth or dare" into my arm.

33:46.915 --> 33:49.483
- Oh, my God, are you okay?
- Y-Yeah.

33:49.485 --> 33:51.785
Yeah, I mean...
it's gone now.

33:51.787 --> 33:54.188
But... I felt it.

33:54.190 --> 33:56.724
Olivia, it was really painful.

33:56.726 --> 33:58.691
Yeah, and when I was
in the library,

33:58.693 --> 34:01.861
I was surrounded by people, but
what we're seeing is not real.

34:01.863 --> 34:03.799
Only the consequences are.

34:05.867 --> 34:07.902
Did you answer?

34:07.904 --> 34:10.841
Lucas, you have to answer.

34:13.509 --> 34:16.545
I've had feelings for Olivia
since we met.

34:22.018 --> 34:24.185
Sometimes I wonder
what it would be like

34:24.187 --> 34:28.121
to be with her
instead of Markie.

34:28.123 --> 34:31.826
And I wonder what it would be
like to wake up next to her...

34:31.828 --> 34:34.828
and kiss her.

34:34.830 --> 34:37.697
But I know
that can never happen.

34:37.699 --> 34:40.603
Oh, God, please tell me
you didn't hang up.

34:44.139 --> 34:46.873
We have to convince
everybody else.

34:46.875 --> 34:48.812
I'm coming.

34:52.982 --> 34:55.982
(DOOR OPENS)

34:55.984 --> 34:58.752
What is all this?

34:58.754 --> 35:01.120
An intervention?

35:01.122 --> 35:03.223
I always thought day-drinking
Penelope would be first.

35:03.225 --> 35:04.525
Thanks.

35:04.527 --> 35:05.960
Thank you for coming.

35:05.962 --> 35:08.895
I live here.

35:08.897 --> 35:11.498
So, what is it all about?

35:11.500 --> 35:13.234
The game.

35:13.236 --> 35:15.935
We're still playing it in the
same order we played in Mexico.

35:15.937 --> 35:18.004
Carter told us the truth;
the game is real.

35:18.006 --> 35:20.674
First, it was my turn,
I got asked in the library, and

35:20.676 --> 35:22.542
it made me tell your secret;
then it was Ronnie's turn,

35:22.544 --> 35:23.944
he didn't do his dare,
and it killed him.

35:23.946 --> 35:25.712
Maybe you and Ronnie
shouldn't have answered.

35:25.714 --> 35:28.082
Carter also said,
"Refuse to play and you die."

35:28.084 --> 35:30.620
I got asked tonight,
and I tried to ignore it.

35:32.721 --> 35:34.721
But then something burned
"truth or dare" on my arm.

35:34.723 --> 35:37.891
Show me.

35:37.893 --> 35:39.759
I mean, it's gone now, but...

35:39.761 --> 35:42.830
- Th-There's nothing there.
- Because I told the truth.

35:42.832 --> 35:46.100
- TYSON: Oh, my God. Geez.
- Wow. Olivia.

35:46.102 --> 35:47.902
I mean, this is next-level.

35:47.904 --> 35:50.737
You can't take responsibility
for humiliating me

35:50.739 --> 35:52.906
in front of everyone
and ruining my relationship,

35:52.908 --> 35:54.942
so you come up
with some insane story

35:54.944 --> 35:56.911
that a game made you say it?

35:56.913 --> 35:59.746
Then you get Lucas
to lie for you.

35:59.748 --> 36:01.549
- No, I'm done.
- Markie.

36:01.551 --> 36:02.886
Markie. Stop.

36:04.219 --> 36:06.853
- You can't be alone.
- Why not?

36:06.855 --> 36:09.089
Because in the picture,
your turn is next.

36:09.091 --> 36:11.027
- (TYSON GROANS)
- (PHONE BUZZING)

36:14.763 --> 36:16.700
Unknown number.
Of course it is.

36:18.600 --> 36:21.601
- "Truth or Dare?" Wow, a text. Really?
- Huh.

36:21.603 --> 36:22.870
I mean, there's no way a human

36:22.872 --> 36:24.904
- could have sent...
- Just answer it.

36:24.906 --> 36:26.774
Fine.

36:26.776 --> 36:28.775
Dare.

36:28.777 --> 36:31.245
"Dare you to follow through
with your promise.

36:31.247 --> 36:33.346
Break Olivia's hand."

36:33.348 --> 36:35.114
Obviously, this was you.

36:35.116 --> 36:37.250
Do you see me
texting you right now?

36:37.252 --> 36:40.120
No, but you were the only one
there when I said that.

36:40.122 --> 36:43.257
Markie, why would I dare you
to break my own hand?

36:43.259 --> 36:45.192
I don't know!
Okay, maybe you're making

36:45.194 --> 36:46.859
a new YouTube video
on how to lose friends.

36:46.861 --> 36:48.097
Oh, that seems
even less likely.

36:49.799 --> 36:52.065
- What are you doing?
- You have to do it.

36:52.067 --> 36:53.801
What?

36:53.803 --> 36:56.038
(PANTING) You have to.

36:57.973 --> 37:01.040
Ronnie didn't do his dare,
and now he's dead.

37:01.042 --> 37:03.743
- Liv, this is so messed up.
- Even by my standards.

37:03.745 --> 37:06.145
Look, as pissed as I am
at you right now...

37:06.147 --> 37:09.216
and I'm so pissed... there's no
way I'm gonna break your hand.

37:09.218 --> 37:11.118
Well, you don't really
have a choice.

37:11.120 --> 37:13.821
So just take it. Please.

37:13.823 --> 37:17.027
Markie, I don't want to find
out what happens if you don't.

37:18.893 --> 37:20.863
(CHUCKLES) Just do it.

37:29.739 --> 37:32.172
- No, I-I can't.
- God, just trust me, Markie!

37:32.174 --> 37:34.143
Do it. Please.

37:38.147 --> 37:40.683
Oh, don't tell me you're
a fucking coward like your dad.

37:41.317 --> 37:42.281
(SCREAMS)

37:42.283 --> 37:44.685
(SOBBING)

37:44.687 --> 37:46.286
Oh, oh, my God.

37:46.288 --> 37:47.855
I'll get some ice.

37:47.857 --> 37:49.723
I can't deal
with this crazy right now.

37:49.725 --> 37:51.158
I got a med school
interview tomorrow.

37:51.160 --> 37:52.359
Uh, see a doctor.

37:52.361 --> 37:54.862
- I'm sorry. Sorry.
- Guys!

37:54.864 --> 37:58.065
Look, we got to go
to the hospital, okay? Come on.

37:58.067 --> 38:00.003
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

38:02.738 --> 38:05.274
BRAD:
<i>You believe all this?</i>

38:07.243 --> 38:10.444
I don't know what to believe.

38:10.446 --> 38:12.382
(WOMAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER P.A.)

38:27.029 --> 38:29.132
(COINS CLINKING)

38:35.805 --> 38:37.841
(MACHINE WHIRS)

38:39.875 --> 38:42.245
Come on.

38:45.413 --> 38:47.049
(HITTING MACHINE)

38:51.986 --> 38:53.922
♪ ♪

39:05.935 --> 39:07.737
(SIGHS)

39:14.843 --> 39:16.712
(DISTORTED CHUCKLE)

39:19.013 --> 39:20.783
(DOOR CLOSES)

39:27.756 --> 39:29.024
(DEMONIC VOICE):
Brad.

39:31.060 --> 39:33.328
Truth or dare?

39:40.102 --> 39:41.100
Brad.

39:41.102 --> 39:43.439
- (YELLS)
- Truth!

39:46.007 --> 39:48.944
(DISTORTED LAUGHING)

39:56.018 --> 39:57.817
- CHANG: Brad?
- (GASPS)

39:57.819 --> 39:59.853
Hi.

39:59.855 --> 40:02.188
- What are you doing here?
- Uh, my job.

40:02.190 --> 40:04.190
Why are you here?

40:04.192 --> 40:06.292
Friend of mine got hurt.
It's nothing serious.

40:06.294 --> 40:09.198
I'm just here for...
for moral support.

40:11.933 --> 40:14.467
CHANG:
Something wrong?

40:14.469 --> 40:19.138
Yeah, no, I'm just, uh...
I'm just a little shaken up.

40:19.140 --> 40:21.841
You haven't come by to see
your mother in a few weeks.

40:21.843 --> 40:23.143
Yeah, I know. I'm sorry.

40:23.145 --> 40:24.944
I thought I was paying
for this school

40:24.946 --> 40:26.946
so you could come home
every once in a while.

40:26.948 --> 40:28.915
I-I know, I know, I just...

40:28.917 --> 40:31.185
Things have been
a little crazy lately.

40:31.187 --> 40:34.022
You know, I don't want
to hear excuses, son.

40:35.890 --> 40:37.826
(DISTORTED):
I want the truth.

40:40.428 --> 40:43.429
There goes another thousand
dollars in credit card debt.

40:43.431 --> 40:45.299
LUCAS:
Oh, my God, Liv.

40:45.301 --> 40:47.301
I just had my turn.

40:47.303 --> 40:49.169
- You what?
- The game.

40:49.171 --> 40:52.239
It made me, um,
it made me come out.

40:52.241 --> 40:55.442
To my father.

40:55.444 --> 40:57.781
Wha... Are you okay?

40:59.214 --> 41:00.913
Yeah.

41:00.915 --> 41:02.583
Yeah. Yeah.

41:02.585 --> 41:05.953
For the first time in my life,
I... I told him my truth

41:05.955 --> 41:08.487
and I stood up to him,
and I feel...

41:08.489 --> 41:10.489
I feel awesome.

41:10.491 --> 41:14.127
Okay, hold on, your dad
didn't know that you were gay?

41:14.129 --> 41:16.362
Your ringtone's Beyoncé.

41:16.364 --> 41:18.098
Everyone loves Beyoncé.

41:18.100 --> 41:20.036
Tyson's next.

41:24.973 --> 41:26.408
(PHONE BUZZES)

41:36.218 --> 41:38.451
WOMAN:
Will do.

41:38.453 --> 41:40.453
Tyson Curran?

41:40.455 --> 41:43.091
Let's do this.

41:46.895 --> 41:48.832
Right this way.

41:53.067 --> 41:56.036
So, you come from
a family of doctors, then?

41:56.038 --> 41:59.473
Yes, ma'am. Mother, father,
sister, uncle and grandfather.

41:59.475 --> 42:01.007
Pretty much everybody.

42:01.009 --> 42:02.509
Well, they must have
set a great example

42:02.511 --> 42:04.411
for you to want
to take the same route.

42:04.413 --> 42:05.978
Yes, uh, absolutely,
Dean Spencer.

42:05.980 --> 42:07.980
You know, uh, growing up,

42:07.982 --> 42:10.449
I would hear their stories
about saving lives,

42:10.451 --> 42:12.618
and... I think...

42:12.620 --> 42:15.524
I think that somehow
shaped me.

42:19.194 --> 42:21.127
Pen. Where's Tyson?

42:21.129 --> 42:23.498
His med school interview. Why?

42:26.435 --> 42:29.002
You know...

42:29.004 --> 42:31.404
I could do something...

42:31.406 --> 42:34.207
self-serving, like become
a hedge fund manager.

42:34.209 --> 42:38.210
The thing is, people need help,
especially in times like these.

42:38.212 --> 42:40.013
That's very noble of you.

42:40.015 --> 42:43.016
You know...

42:43.018 --> 42:45.421
I just have one final question.

42:47.388 --> 42:49.325
♪ ♪

42:55.129 --> 42:56.231
(GASPS)

42:58.267 --> 43:00.967
(SIGHS)
He hasn't had his turn yet.

43:00.969 --> 43:02.402
Mr. Curran?

43:02.404 --> 43:04.172
Your bag.

43:08.176 --> 43:10.409
- Wait, Tyson, no. Wait, Tyson!
- Hey!

43:10.411 --> 43:11.381
Can I help you?

43:18.988 --> 43:20.654
(DISTORTED):
Truth or dare?

43:20.656 --> 43:23.457
I'm sorry, I beg your pardon?

43:23.459 --> 43:25.759
Truth or dare?

43:25.761 --> 43:28.261
Truth, I guess.

43:28.263 --> 43:31.230
(CHUCKLES) Did my friends
really put you up to this?

43:31.232 --> 43:33.132
How long have you been
forging prescriptions?

43:33.134 --> 43:35.971
I don't.

43:38.540 --> 43:40.440
Did she actually tell you that?

43:40.442 --> 43:42.542
- Excuse me?
- I don't forge prescriptions.

43:42.544 --> 43:44.714
Why would you even ask me that?

43:47.082 --> 43:49.016
Um...

43:49.018 --> 43:51.350
- Ty! Ty! Ty! Open the door!
- Hey! Hey! - Hey, Tyson!

43:51.352 --> 43:54.654
- (MUFFLED SHOUTING)
- (DOOR RATTLING)

43:54.656 --> 43:56.390
- Tyson! - Tyson!
- Are you okay?

43:56.392 --> 43:58.091
- Open the door!
- Ty! - Ty! Hey!

43:58.093 --> 43:59.259
What are you doing?

43:59.261 --> 44:02.362
Oh! Oh, my... Oh, my God!

44:02.364 --> 44:04.698
(SCREAMING)
Oh, my God!

44:04.700 --> 44:06.201
My God!

44:08.803 --> 44:11.973
(SCREAMING)

44:16.044 --> 44:18.645
Tyson lied
and then died because of it.

44:18.647 --> 44:22.214
Just like Ronnie did
when he didn't do the dare.

44:22.216 --> 44:24.216
Then my turn's next.

44:24.218 --> 44:26.420
Yeah, pick truth.

44:26.422 --> 44:28.821
I mean, listen,
we-we all should, right?

44:28.823 --> 44:30.457
And then whatever question
that we get asked,

44:30.459 --> 44:32.058
we just answer it
with a hundred percent honesty.

44:32.060 --> 44:33.627
Okay? That's how
we're gonna survive

44:33.629 --> 44:35.364
till we figure this out.

44:37.332 --> 44:41.036
We got it?
Only choose truth.

44:42.337 --> 44:44.136
PENELOPE:
<i>Need more vodka.</i>

44:44.138 --> 44:46.573
You need sleep.

44:46.575 --> 44:49.408
Okay, I'll put her in bed.

44:49.410 --> 44:51.210
You guys find Carter.

44:51.212 --> 44:54.182
He started all this.
Maybe he can end it.

45:02.524 --> 45:04.093
He said that he went to USC.

45:06.661 --> 45:09.429
Five Carters,
none of them our guy.

45:09.431 --> 45:11.698
Maybe he meant the other USC.

45:11.700 --> 45:14.234
All right, she's asleep.
Did you find Carter yet?

45:14.236 --> 45:17.239
- No. Dead end.
- Did you try using Google?

45:18.674 --> 45:21.244
Search "Mexico truth or dare."

45:30.185 --> 45:31.621
(SIGHS)

45:34.556 --> 45:36.192
(GROANS SOFTLY)

45:40.728 --> 45:42.462
(SIGHS)

45:42.464 --> 45:44.400
♪ ♪

45:51.239 --> 45:52.841
(EXHALES)

45:59.814 --> 46:01.583
Uh, guys?

46:06.221 --> 46:09.556
"Suspect Giselle Hammond, 22,
an American college student,

46:09.558 --> 46:13.493
"had gone missing while on
spring break in Rosarito Beach.

46:13.495 --> 46:15.428
"The clerk recounted
Hammond's bizarre behavior

46:15.430 --> 46:17.563
"before the incident,

46:17.565 --> 46:19.602
which is backed up
with surveillance footage."

46:20.736 --> 46:22.536
GISELLE:
Pack of Morleys.

46:22.538 --> 46:24.837
- (CLERK SPEAKS SPANISH)
- I don't want to play anymore.

46:24.839 --> 46:26.741
CLERK:
<i>¿Va a ser cash o crédito?</i>

46:27.843 --> 46:29.277
Dare.

46:30.745 --> 46:32.645
CLERK:
<i>Señorita. Qué...</i>

46:32.647 --> 46:34.249
<i>Perdón.</i>

46:36.350 --> 46:38.350
- WOMAN: No!
- GISELLE: I'm sorry, I don't have a choice.

46:38.352 --> 46:39.788
- Holy shit.
- (FIRE WHOOSHES, WOMAN SCREAMS)

46:42.823 --> 46:44.958
- LUCAS: Did they catch her?
- MARKIE: Uh...

46:44.960 --> 46:47.497
No, no, it says there's
still an ongoing search.

46:49.864 --> 46:51.466
I just found her on Facebook.

46:59.373 --> 47:01.875
- Oh, my God, it's him.
- BRAD: Is he tagged?

47:01.877 --> 47:03.877
No, I don't see him
in any other photos.

47:03.879 --> 47:05.679
Look at her wall.
Maybe he posted.

47:05.681 --> 47:06.946
OLIVIA:
Well, not that I see.

47:06.948 --> 47:08.815
But... there's a bunch of posts

47:08.817 --> 47:10.549
about people asking her
to turn herself in,

47:10.551 --> 47:12.451
stuff like that.

47:12.453 --> 47:14.453
Wait, do you think
she's checking this?

47:14.455 --> 47:16.989
- DM her.
- Wait.

47:16.991 --> 47:19.926
Just, uh, make a fake account.

47:19.928 --> 47:23.299
- We don't want this shit traced to us.
- Yeah.

47:25.834 --> 47:29.236
So, we're here on
our first vacation together.

47:29.238 --> 47:30.870
- Is it our first vacation together? Kinda?
- The beach.

47:30.872 --> 47:33.473
PENELOPE: Um, I mean, there was
that time you came and visited

47:33.475 --> 47:35.542
me and my family in Texas,

47:35.544 --> 47:37.509
- but...
- You're from Texas?

47:37.511 --> 47:40.513
I thought you were from Mexico.

47:40.515 --> 47:42.515
PENELOPE (LAUGHS):
I'm not from Mexico!

47:42.517 --> 47:44.250
- Tyson!
- (VIDEO STOPS)

47:44.252 --> 47:45.854
(SIGHS)

47:50.491 --> 47:51.757
(VOMITS)

47:51.759 --> 47:55.995
We're playing the game, too.

47:55.997 --> 47:58.797
We need your help.

47:58.799 --> 48:01.268
- Please meet me.
- This woman is wanted for murder.

48:01.270 --> 48:03.770
Do you really think she's gonna
come out of hiding for

48:03.772 --> 48:05.708
"We need your help"?

48:07.743 --> 48:10.712
I know the game dared you
to set that woman on fire.

48:12.013 --> 48:14.513
Tell me where to meet you,

48:14.515 --> 48:16.750
or I'll wait outside
your family's house

48:16.752 --> 48:19.752
until the game dares me
to do the same to them.

48:19.754 --> 48:21.420
Markie, you cannot send that.

48:21.422 --> 48:24.024
If you want to live,
you need to stop thinking

48:24.026 --> 48:27.263
about other people and start
thinking about yourself.

48:39.073 --> 48:40.742
(EXHALES)

48:44.745 --> 48:46.281
(GASPS)

48:50.718 --> 48:53.420
(DISTORTED):
Truth or dare, beautiful?

48:53.422 --> 48:55.621
(PANTING)

48:55.623 --> 48:58.324
What? Hard to make a decision

48:58.326 --> 49:00.592
without Tyson telling you
what to do?

49:00.594 --> 49:03.663
Screw you.

49:03.665 --> 49:05.065
Truth.

49:05.067 --> 49:06.933
Truth or dare?

49:06.935 --> 49:08.801
I said truth.

49:08.803 --> 49:10.670
Sorry.

49:10.672 --> 49:13.540
That's not how this game works.

49:13.542 --> 49:16.645
What the hell
is that supposed to mean?

49:18.379 --> 49:20.112
(OLIVIA SIGHS)

49:20.114 --> 49:22.348
LUCAS:
Be patient. She'll write back.

49:22.350 --> 49:23.885
This is all my fault.

49:25.886 --> 49:27.823
- Hey, no, it's not.
- No, she's right.

49:29.924 --> 49:32.725
None of us wanted
to follow that creep.

49:32.727 --> 49:34.993
None of us wanted to play
that stupid game.

49:34.995 --> 49:38.464
The only reason I went
on that trip was for you.

49:38.466 --> 49:40.033
Remember?
You said you needed

49:40.035 --> 49:41.768
- your best friend.
- BRAD: All right, come on...

49:41.770 --> 49:43.603
No, but now I realize
it's not about friendship

49:43.605 --> 49:45.871
or "I choose you,"
it was about me being there

49:45.873 --> 49:47.873
to cover your ass while
you hooked up with randoms!

49:47.875 --> 49:49.578
Hey.

49:52.681 --> 49:54.483
Screw you, Olivia.

49:57.085 --> 49:59.451
- Was that necessary?
- (DOOR CLOSES)

49:59.453 --> 50:01.487
Guys. Come outside.

50:01.489 --> 50:03.022
Now!

50:03.024 --> 50:04.993
(WHISPERS):
Shit.

50:07.596 --> 50:09.596
OLIVIA:
Pen? What are you doing?

50:09.598 --> 50:12.031
(CRYING): I tried.
It wouldn't let me pick truth.

50:12.033 --> 50:13.933
I tried, I swear!

50:13.935 --> 50:15.969
(PANTING)

50:15.971 --> 50:19.438
I have to walk the edge
until I finish this.

50:19.440 --> 50:20.707
(PENELOPE SOBBING)

50:20.709 --> 50:22.544
OLIVIA:
Pen, you're gonna be fine.

50:25.614 --> 50:28.681
Okay, just go slow.
Take your time.

50:28.683 --> 50:31.650
- Oh! - MARKIE: Be careful!
- I'm gonna go up there.

50:31.652 --> 50:32.986
I'll try and grab her
if she loses her balance.

50:32.988 --> 50:35.754
No, your hand's broken.
I'll go.

50:35.756 --> 50:37.757
Pen, just walk slowly, okay?

50:37.759 --> 50:40.025
- (BREATH TREMBLING)
- Hey!

50:40.027 --> 50:42.127
Just take your time, okay?
Walk slowly.

50:42.129 --> 50:43.562
It's gonna be fine.

50:43.564 --> 50:44.663
- BRAD: What do we do?
- Be careful.

50:44.665 --> 50:45.864
It's gonna be okay.

50:45.866 --> 50:48.600
BRAD:
You're gonna be okay.

50:48.602 --> 50:50.770
We need to grab something
in case she falls. Go inside.

50:50.772 --> 50:52.504
- I'm gonna clear a path.
- All right, let's go, let's go,

50:52.506 --> 50:54.507
let's go, let's go!

50:54.509 --> 50:55.945
(BREATH TREMBLING)

51:03.518 --> 51:06.986
- (SCREAMS, GASPS)
- Pen? Be careful.

51:06.988 --> 51:09.656
- You're good, okay?
- Hey, will this work?

51:09.658 --> 51:12.125
What? Yeah. Yeah. Come on.

51:12.127 --> 51:14.861
Just get under her.

51:14.863 --> 51:17.029
- Get under her and follow her.
- BRAD: Be careful, Pen.

51:17.031 --> 51:19.699
- Oh, sh...
- OLIVIA: Get back. Get back, get back.

51:19.701 --> 51:21.634
No need to rush.

51:21.636 --> 51:22.969
(WHIMPERING)

51:22.971 --> 51:25.571
MARKIE:
It's okay. It's okay, Pen.

51:25.573 --> 51:27.742
OLIVIA: Just take your time.
Take it slowly.

51:29.944 --> 51:32.814
OLIVIA: Pen, just put one foot
in front of the other.

51:36.250 --> 51:37.620
(PENELOPE GASPS)

51:39.654 --> 51:41.687
OLIVIA:
Watch it, okay? Just go slow.

51:41.689 --> 51:43.556
You can do this.

51:43.558 --> 51:45.895
We're right here.
We're here for you, okay?

51:51.665 --> 51:53.766
OLIVIA:
I see her. She's right there.

51:53.768 --> 51:55.171
Go. Go. Go.

51:57.239 --> 52:00.272
- W-Wait, she's on the corner.
- BRAD: There she is.

52:00.274 --> 52:02.208
(PENELOPE CRYING)

52:02.210 --> 52:03.909
Get that stuff out of the way.

52:03.911 --> 52:05.645
(GASPING)

52:05.647 --> 52:07.583
(GRUNTING)

52:11.018 --> 52:13.920
Pen! Pen.

52:13.922 --> 52:16.255
I'm coming. I'm coming.

52:16.257 --> 52:17.723
(GASPS)

52:17.725 --> 52:19.725
No, no, no,
don't get too close.

52:19.727 --> 52:21.995
If I, if I, if I cheat,
if I don't do the dare...

52:21.997 --> 52:24.531
I know. I know. Okay?

52:24.533 --> 52:27.799
But when you finish,
I'll be here to grab you.

52:27.801 --> 52:29.671
Just got to go around
this corner now, okay?

52:31.038 --> 52:33.508
(PENELOPE CRYING)

52:40.015 --> 52:41.781
(EXHALES):
Oh.

52:41.783 --> 52:43.815
- (GRUNTING)
- (GATE RATTLING)

52:43.817 --> 52:45.754
MARKIE:
Come on.

52:47.288 --> 52:50.790
Take your time, okay?

52:50.792 --> 52:53.158
(GRUNTS)

52:53.160 --> 52:55.594
You're doing great, Pen.

52:55.596 --> 52:57.830
- Don't look down.
- Wait. Stay here. Stay below her.

52:57.832 --> 53:00.132
MARKIE: Okay.
Wait, where are you going?

53:00.134 --> 53:02.167
Hey, Pen.
Don't look at the fence.

53:02.169 --> 53:04.670
Okay? Look at me.
Okay? You're almost there.

53:04.672 --> 53:05.841
Just a little more.

53:16.051 --> 53:18.250
(PANTING)

53:18.252 --> 53:20.752
She's right above us.
Throw it on top.

53:20.754 --> 53:21.789
- MARKIE: You ready?
- Yeah.

53:24.926 --> 53:27.092
- That's not gonna work.
- (TIRES SCREECHING)

53:27.094 --> 53:28.663
(VEHICLE APPROACHING)

53:31.031 --> 53:33.366
- That might.
- (TIRES SCREECHING)

53:33.368 --> 53:34.837
(BRAD GRUNTS)

53:39.607 --> 53:41.040
- Whoa!
- Hey! Penelope!

53:41.042 --> 53:43.279
(WHISPERS):
Shit.

53:44.613 --> 53:46.946
(TIRES SCREECH)

53:46.948 --> 53:48.815
Guys, get back further!

53:48.817 --> 53:50.382
- Go, go, go, move back.
- Get back!

53:50.384 --> 53:52.185
One last sip.

53:52.187 --> 53:53.955
(TIRES SCREECHING)

54:05.332 --> 54:07.902
No, no, Pen! Hey, Pen! No! No!

54:10.404 --> 54:13.239
- Pen?
- MARKIE: She's not moving.

54:13.241 --> 54:14.243
Pen?

54:16.210 --> 54:18.814
(PENELOPE GROANING)

54:22.716 --> 54:24.884
Is this my bed?

54:24.886 --> 54:26.355
(CHUCKLES)

54:27.321 --> 54:29.688
(VOMITING LOUDLY)

54:29.690 --> 54:31.290
Yeah.

54:31.292 --> 54:33.862
- You're okay.
- (PHONE BUZZING)

54:36.964 --> 54:40.234
I just got a Facebook message
from Giselle.

54:41.969 --> 54:43.906
♪ ♪

54:55.049 --> 54:58.350
We're sure this is a good idea,
meeting her here?

54:58.352 --> 54:59.752
What if the cops
trace her message?

54:59.754 --> 55:01.154
No, she wrote us
on a fake account.

55:01.156 --> 55:03.156
Yeah, but that chick
lit somebody on fire.

55:03.158 --> 55:05.024
- She's probably nuts.
- MARKIE: I mean,

55:05.026 --> 55:06.395
- do we really have another choice?
- (KNOCKING)

55:14.368 --> 55:16.736
I mean, we can talk
about this inside. Come on.

55:16.738 --> 55:18.304
(SNIFFS)

55:18.306 --> 55:20.242
Let's go.

55:22.343 --> 55:24.409
Inside?

55:24.411 --> 55:26.446
Uh-uh. Okay, all right,
that's far enough.

55:26.448 --> 55:28.080
Can you tell us
what's happening?

55:28.082 --> 55:30.348
- Which one of you is Olivia?
- No, you answer

55:30.350 --> 55:32.018
our question first:
How do you know Carter?

55:32.020 --> 55:33.351
- Carter?
- MARKIE: You know, cut the crap.

55:33.353 --> 55:34.319
We saw the photo.

55:34.321 --> 55:36.855
He's the one who brought us
into this game.

55:36.857 --> 55:37.924
Uh, yeah, right, okay.

55:37.926 --> 55:40.359
- Carter, right.
- Did he bring you into this, too?

55:40.361 --> 55:42.228
N-No, uh, he didn't,
he didn't start this.

55:42.230 --> 55:43.462
He was just one of my friends.

55:43.464 --> 55:46.933
We-we all went on a trip to
Mexico and got really wasted.

55:46.935 --> 55:50.002
We-we found this old church,
and we decided to party in it,

55:50.004 --> 55:52.170
and my roommate wanted to play
Truth or Dare, so we did,

55:52.172 --> 55:54.406
but when we got home, the game,
it just, it kept going.

55:54.408 --> 55:56.174
My roommate died first,
and then the other ones...

55:56.176 --> 55:59.112
- How is this possible?
- I wish I knew.

55:59.114 --> 56:01.047
You know, I thought
this was some kind of, like,

56:01.049 --> 56:03.015
karmic payback for Sam
trashing the place, you know?

56:03.017 --> 56:05.150
- Sam?
- Uh, yeah, Sam.

56:05.152 --> 56:07.018
He-he was...
one of my friends.

56:07.020 --> 56:09.187
He-he got really drunk, and
he just started breaking stuff.

56:09.189 --> 56:11.824
I don't know, we were, we were
all being idiots. (SIGHS)

56:11.826 --> 56:13.893
Our friend
just had a turn in the game.

56:13.895 --> 56:16.362
It wouldn't let her pick truth.
Do you know why?

56:16.364 --> 56:17.797
It's how we played.

56:17.799 --> 56:19.464
We called it
two truths and a dare.

56:19.466 --> 56:21.466
If... if two people
picked truth in a row,

56:21.468 --> 56:23.435
then the next person
had to do a dare.

56:23.437 --> 56:25.471
(CHUCKLES): Thought it was
more fun that way.

56:25.473 --> 56:29.275
More fun? Your asshole buddy
gave us a death sentence.

56:29.277 --> 56:31.076
Any more super dangerous rules
you want to tell us about?

56:31.078 --> 56:33.312
Easy, Pen.

56:33.314 --> 56:35.882
He-he told me he was dared
to find a new group to play,

56:35.884 --> 56:37.482
and that it had to be
at the mission.

56:37.484 --> 56:39.152
He didn't have a choice,
you know?

56:39.154 --> 56:40.987
Of course he did.

56:40.989 --> 56:42.989
Okay, so where is Carter now?

56:42.991 --> 56:44.891
I haven't talked to him
since he went back to Mexico.

56:44.893 --> 56:47.859
I thought that when he got
a new group to play

56:47.861 --> 56:49.895
that we-we would be out.
I can't believe he only got

56:49.897 --> 56:52.198
five of you to play.
If he would've got more,

56:52.200 --> 56:55.167
then I would've had a longer
time before I had to go again.

56:55.169 --> 56:57.435
You got another turn?

56:57.437 --> 56:59.471
Okay, it's time to go, guys.

56:59.473 --> 57:01.040
Is this why
you're telling us the truth?

57:01.042 --> 57:04.243
No, I, uh... I picked dare.

57:04.245 --> 57:06.078
Markie's right.
Let's get out of here.

57:06.080 --> 57:08.116
Okay, we're leaving.
Come on, Olivia.

57:10.185 --> 57:12.884
I am so sorry, Olivia.

57:12.886 --> 57:15.453
How did you know my name
when I got here?

57:15.455 --> 57:18.026
I... I didn't put it
in the message.

57:19.326 --> 57:20.826
No! No!

57:20.828 --> 57:23.196
- LUCAS: No! Pen!
- MARKIE: Pen!

57:23.198 --> 57:24.931
No! No!

57:24.933 --> 57:26.866
- (GUNSHOT)
- (GASPS)

57:26.868 --> 57:28.234
(GRUNTING)

57:28.236 --> 57:30.335
- Hold her down!
- I have to kill Olivia!

57:30.337 --> 57:32.304
Hold her down!

57:32.306 --> 57:34.243
- BRAD: Grab the gun.
- (LUCAS GRUNTING)

57:36.343 --> 57:38.844
BRAD:
Stop moving.

57:38.846 --> 57:40.515
What the...?

57:42.183 --> 57:44.116
LUCAS:
What? No! No!

57:44.118 --> 57:47.085
- (GRUNTING)
- No! No! No!

57:47.087 --> 57:48.987
- (GUNSHOT)
- (GASPS)

57:48.989 --> 57:50.459
BRAD:
Oh, shit.

57:52.926 --> 57:55.027
(BREATH TREMBLING)

57:55.029 --> 57:57.964
What was she thinking?

57:57.966 --> 58:00.199
It wasn't her.
(SNIFFS)

58:00.201 --> 58:02.201
Something took over,
like she was possessed.

58:02.203 --> 58:04.103
She didn't finish her dare.

58:04.105 --> 58:06.272
Like Ronnie.

58:06.274 --> 58:08.540
This is what happens.

58:08.542 --> 58:10.478
So what do we do?

58:13.080 --> 58:15.017
We tell the truth.

58:20.321 --> 58:22.154
(CRYING QUIETLY)

58:22.156 --> 58:25.491
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

58:25.493 --> 58:27.158
- Yeah, right away.
- OLIVIA: <i>She was erratic,</i>

58:27.160 --> 58:28.560
<i>said she had to kill me.</i>

58:28.562 --> 58:30.562
Then Penelope
pushed me out of the way,

58:30.564 --> 58:32.431
she shot her and then
turned the gun on herself.

58:32.433 --> 58:34.634
Were you aware that Giselle
Hammond was wanted for murder?

58:34.636 --> 58:38.203
Yes. Yeah, we thought
that she knew someone

58:38.205 --> 58:40.473
that we were looking for,
a guy that we met in Mexico.

58:40.475 --> 58:43.475
- His name was Carter.
- You don't know his last name?

58:43.477 --> 58:45.243
No.

58:45.245 --> 58:48.983
Any of these people
look like him?

58:56.290 --> 58:58.324
No. Who are they?

58:58.326 --> 59:01.460
Five of Giselle Hammond's
friends... all deceased.

59:01.462 --> 59:05.167
Three suicides, two accidental
deaths, all in three weeks.

59:06.701 --> 59:09.402
And now you've lost
two friends.

59:09.404 --> 59:12.404
I don't believe
in coincidences, Olivia.

59:12.406 --> 59:14.073
I think this is all connected.

59:14.075 --> 59:16.141
If you know how,
you need to tell me.

59:16.143 --> 59:18.310
No, I promise.

59:18.312 --> 59:20.946
If I did know, I would.

59:20.948 --> 59:23.251
I hope so.

59:29.457 --> 59:31.324
We'll be in touch.

59:31.326 --> 59:34.429
Don't take any more vacations.

59:37.064 --> 59:38.998
That did not go well.

59:39.000 --> 59:40.665
LUCAS:
We told them the truth.

59:40.667 --> 59:42.268
As much as we could.

59:42.270 --> 59:44.103
Guys, the cops should be
the least of our concerns.

59:44.105 --> 59:47.640
I mean, Penelope's dead
and Giselle gave us nothing.

59:47.642 --> 59:50.643
She did say a new game
had to start at the mission.

59:50.645 --> 59:52.645
That place has to be the key.

59:52.647 --> 59:55.580
CHANG:
Brad.

59:55.582 --> 59:57.750
(SIGHS) Catch up
with you guys later.

59:57.752 --> 59:59.284
- No, we shouldn't split up.
- No, it's okay.

59:59.286 --> 01:00:00.553
My turn's not for a while.

01:00:00.555 --> 01:00:05.123
I'll deal with my father; you
deal with finding the mission.

01:00:05.125 --> 01:00:07.062
Come on.

01:00:11.265 --> 01:00:12.667
I think it was built in 1896.

01:00:14.167 --> 01:00:16.335
Yeah, that really
narrows it down.

01:00:16.337 --> 01:00:18.536
It's a start.

01:00:18.538 --> 01:00:21.073
Oh, shit.
I got to grab my charger.

01:00:21.075 --> 01:00:23.011
Uh, I think you left
your bag in my room.

01:00:24.411 --> 01:00:25.680
(LUCAS CLEARS THROAT)

01:00:39.527 --> 01:00:41.697
♪ ♪

01:00:55.076 --> 01:00:56.308
- Oh, my God.
- What?

01:00:56.310 --> 01:00:58.680
Check this out.

01:01:01.314 --> 01:01:05.116
It says there was a massacre
a few weeks later.

01:01:05.118 --> 01:01:09.323
Only one survivor, lives in
the area, Inez Reyes, 19.

01:01:16.631 --> 01:01:19.401
(DOOR CREAKING)

01:01:38.218 --> 01:01:41.422
♪ ♪

01:01:47.594 --> 01:01:49.795
(SCREAMING)

01:01:49.797 --> 01:01:54.403
(DEMONIC VOICE):
Truth or dare?

01:01:59.707 --> 01:02:02.310
(OLIVIA SHOUTING)

01:02:04.178 --> 01:02:07.745
Where is she? Liv!

01:02:07.747 --> 01:02:09.415
- Hey! Hey!
- (OLIVA YELLS) - Olivia.

01:02:09.417 --> 01:02:11.484
- Are you okay?
- Where am I?

01:02:11.486 --> 01:02:13.351
- Where am I?!
- What the hell are you...?

01:02:13.353 --> 01:02:15.286
Who the... Hey, hey, hey!

01:02:15.288 --> 01:02:16.654
Hey!

01:02:16.656 --> 01:02:18.656
- Are you okay?
- (PANTING)

01:02:18.658 --> 01:02:20.525
Was that your turn?

01:02:20.527 --> 01:02:22.495
LUCAS:
Hey, hey, come back!

01:02:22.497 --> 01:02:24.332
Come back!

01:02:28.136 --> 01:02:31.469
Olivia, what did he say?

01:02:31.471 --> 01:02:35.241
(PANTING)

01:02:35.243 --> 01:02:37.846
He dared me
to sleep with Lucas.

01:02:40.147 --> 01:02:42.281
Why would you pick dare?

01:02:42.283 --> 01:02:44.283
Because of what Giselle said.

01:02:44.285 --> 01:02:45.783
I-If I picked truth,

01:02:45.785 --> 01:02:48.756
I was just forcing
someone else to pick dare.

01:02:52.292 --> 01:02:54.395
How noble.

01:02:56.397 --> 01:02:59.230
Markie, I didn't know
that's what it would ask.

01:02:59.232 --> 01:03:01.799
I don't think
he knew where he was.

01:03:01.801 --> 01:03:03.636
- Are you guys okay?
- Yeah, I'm perfect.

01:03:03.638 --> 01:03:05.337
Well, hey, hey.
Where are you going?

01:03:05.339 --> 01:03:07.672
- Anywhere but here.
- What is going on?

01:03:07.674 --> 01:03:10.312
Why don't you ask Olivia?

01:03:16.183 --> 01:03:20.154
Will you please tell me
what the hell is going on?

01:03:25.792 --> 01:03:27.792
I got my turn.

01:03:27.794 --> 01:03:29.497
Yeah, and?

01:03:38.205 --> 01:03:41.209
Mm, oh, hey, no.
Wh-What are we doing?

01:03:45.245 --> 01:03:47.779
Oh, this is the dare.

01:03:47.781 --> 01:03:49.681
I'm sorry.

01:03:49.683 --> 01:03:51.616
Why didn't you pick truth?

01:03:51.618 --> 01:03:54.620
I told Markie it was so that
you guys wouldn't have to,

01:03:54.622 --> 01:03:56.788
but that was a lie.

01:03:56.790 --> 01:03:58.623
I chose dare because
there is something

01:03:58.625 --> 01:04:00.259
that I can never tell Markie,

01:04:00.261 --> 01:04:02.728
and I'm really afraid
the game's gonna make me do it.

01:04:02.730 --> 01:04:03.895
It can't be that bad.

01:04:03.897 --> 01:04:06.431
(SIGHS)

01:04:06.433 --> 01:04:08.335
You have no idea.

01:04:10.638 --> 01:04:12.741
♪ ♪

01:04:20.614 --> 01:04:22.681
- (GRUNTS)
- What?

01:04:22.683 --> 01:04:24.382
(PANTING)

01:04:24.384 --> 01:04:26.451
No, you are just doing this
because of the dare,

01:04:26.453 --> 01:04:27.752
because you have to.

01:04:27.754 --> 01:04:30.656
No, you have to.

01:04:30.658 --> 01:04:32.326
I don't.

01:04:35.462 --> 01:04:37.399
♪ ♪

01:04:46.506 --> 01:04:48.842
(BOTH PANTING)

01:05:05.593 --> 01:05:07.792
(GRUNTS)

01:05:07.794 --> 01:05:09.730
(DISTORTED):
Look at me.

01:05:13.567 --> 01:05:14.902
Truth or dare?

01:05:17.038 --> 01:05:20.038
Truth or dare?

01:05:20.040 --> 01:05:21.774
Tr-Truth!

01:05:21.776 --> 01:05:24.042
Who are you truly in love with?

01:05:24.044 --> 01:05:25.546
(PANTING)

01:05:30.451 --> 01:05:33.488
I care about you. I do.

01:05:35.455 --> 01:05:37.892
I'm in love with Markie.

01:05:41.895 --> 01:05:44.596
Liv, I'm sorry.
It was the game.

01:05:44.598 --> 01:05:47.701
No, it was the truth.

01:05:52.806 --> 01:05:56.578
(RINGTONE PLAYING)

01:06:02.415 --> 01:06:04.352
♪ ♪

01:06:15.462 --> 01:06:17.763
MARKIE (OVER SPEAKER):
Roy Cameron, 45 years old,

01:06:17.765 --> 01:06:19.665
attempts to make dinner.

01:06:19.667 --> 01:06:21.433
Take one.

01:06:21.435 --> 01:06:23.534
Whoa, a little faith, please.

01:06:23.536 --> 01:06:25.603
Nobody makes a steak
like your old man.

01:06:25.605 --> 01:06:27.973
MARKIE:
Wait, Dad, I'm pescatarian now.

01:06:27.975 --> 01:06:30.779
(LAUGHS) I know, honey.

01:06:34.681 --> 01:06:36.382
Dad?

01:06:36.384 --> 01:06:38.753
I miss you so much.

01:06:41.654 --> 01:06:43.654
I miss you, too.

01:06:43.656 --> 01:06:46.991
There's something that
I've been dying to ask you.

01:06:46.993 --> 01:06:48.762
(STATIC CRACKLES)

01:06:50.864 --> 01:06:53.766
(QUIETLY):
No.

01:06:53.768 --> 01:06:56.167
- (LINE RINGING)
- She's not answering.

01:06:56.169 --> 01:06:57.636
Wait. Come here.
Look at this.

01:06:57.638 --> 01:06:59.571
There's no number,
but she lives in Tijuana.

01:06:59.573 --> 01:07:00.906
That's less than
three hours away.

01:07:00.908 --> 01:07:02.775
Who is she?

01:07:02.777 --> 01:07:04.777
She's someone who might
be able to help us.

01:07:04.779 --> 01:07:06.448
Come on.

01:07:12.719 --> 01:07:15.987
ROY (DISTORTED):
Come on, sweetheart.

01:07:15.989 --> 01:07:18.424
- Time to pick.
- (STATIC CRACKLES)

01:07:18.426 --> 01:07:20.958
Truth.

01:07:20.960 --> 01:07:24.562
The gun I used
to kill myself...

01:07:24.564 --> 01:07:26.498
why do you keep it?

01:07:26.500 --> 01:07:29.902
Sometimes I think about
using it.

01:07:29.904 --> 01:07:32.006
Maybe you should get it.

01:07:39.078 --> 01:07:41.045
LUCAS:
<i>I'm worried about Markie.</i>

01:07:41.047 --> 01:07:43.815
I wish we would have
found her before we left.

01:07:43.817 --> 01:07:46.518
Yeah, well, she doesn't want
to speak to me right now,

01:07:46.520 --> 01:07:49.455
so there's nothing we can do.

01:07:49.457 --> 01:07:51.489
(OLIVIA SIGHS)

01:07:51.491 --> 01:07:53.859
You know that secret
that you're keeping from her?

01:07:53.861 --> 01:07:55.560
Maybe if you got it out,

01:07:55.562 --> 01:07:57.696
- the game couldn't use it against you.
- No.

01:07:57.698 --> 01:07:59.598
No one can ever know.

01:07:59.600 --> 01:08:02.667
Especially not Markie.
It would kill her.

01:08:02.669 --> 01:08:05.904
I'll try her again
when we get there.

01:08:05.906 --> 01:08:07.842
♪ ♪

01:08:25.559 --> 01:08:27.529
(CHIMES TINKLING SOFTLY)

01:08:45.946 --> 01:08:48.279
(SPEAKS SPANISH)

01:08:48.282 --> 01:08:50.214
- OLIVIA: Um...
- Can I help you?

01:08:50.216 --> 01:08:52.917
S-Sorry. Um, we're looking
for Inez Reyes.

01:08:52.920 --> 01:08:54.986
She's my grandmother.
I watch after her.

01:08:54.988 --> 01:08:57.154
We were just wondering
if we could speak to her.

01:08:57.157 --> 01:08:59.524
She speaks to no one.

01:08:59.527 --> 01:09:01.593
No. Please!

01:09:01.595 --> 01:09:03.594
Our friends are dying
just like hers did.

01:09:03.595 --> 01:09:05.200
We-we just need a few words.

01:09:08.801 --> 01:09:10.801
I will ask.

01:09:10.804 --> 01:09:14.872
And if you could...
show her this.

01:09:14.875 --> 01:09:17.609
Show her that we were
at this mission

01:09:17.611 --> 01:09:20.877
and that half the people
in this photo are now dead.

01:09:20.880 --> 01:09:22.649
Then maybe she'll talk to us.

01:09:24.751 --> 01:09:28.286
She might see you,
but she will not speak to you.

01:09:28.287 --> 01:09:31.087
She has not said a word
in 50 years.

01:09:31.090 --> 01:09:33.560
Wait here.

01:09:36.662 --> 01:09:40.198
She must have taken
a vow of silence, right?

01:09:40.200 --> 01:09:42.033
She was 19 when her friends
were butchered.

01:09:42.036 --> 01:09:45.238
- Imagine what that did to her.
- I don't have to.

01:09:52.045 --> 01:09:53.981
♪ ♪

01:10:05.925 --> 01:10:07.861
It's been over an hour.

01:10:10.163 --> 01:10:12.164
Yeah, for someone
who doesn't speak,

01:10:12.166 --> 01:10:15.366
they seem to be doing
a lot of talking.

01:10:15.368 --> 01:10:17.671
She will see you.

01:10:20.741 --> 01:10:22.841
I'm sorry for the wait.

01:10:22.843 --> 01:10:25.276
She has written
something for you.

01:10:25.278 --> 01:10:28.045
What is it?

01:10:28.047 --> 01:10:30.848
She would not let me read it.

01:10:30.850 --> 01:10:32.886
(SPEAKS SPANISH)

01:10:37.157 --> 01:10:40.562
Thank you for seeing us,
Miss Reyes.

01:10:57.745 --> 01:10:59.677
"The mission was a convent

01:10:59.679 --> 01:11:01.279
"where young women
went to find God.

01:11:01.281 --> 01:11:05.851
"We were girls, so we played
silly games like Hide and Seek.

01:11:05.853 --> 01:11:07.852
"But the priest
who ran the convent

01:11:07.854 --> 01:11:09.987
"forced us to play
his own game.

01:11:09.989 --> 01:11:12.824
"He let us hide, but then
he took the one he found.

01:11:12.826 --> 01:11:15.363
"His pleasure was our pain.

01:11:16.663 --> 01:11:18.829
"We suffered in silence.

01:11:18.831 --> 01:11:20.265
"Then one of the girls
told a secret.

01:11:20.267 --> 01:11:23.235
"She knew spells
that could call spirits,

01:11:23.237 --> 01:11:26.370
"so she summoned
a demon named Calux.

01:11:26.372 --> 01:11:28.140
He possessed our game."

01:11:28.142 --> 01:11:29.711
Possessed the game?

01:11:41.721 --> 01:11:45.824
"Demons possess people, places,

01:11:45.826 --> 01:11:48.129
objects, even ideas."

01:11:50.229 --> 01:11:51.797
Uh, uh...

01:11:51.799 --> 01:11:53.231
"Calux is a trickster.

01:11:53.233 --> 01:11:55.299
"That night, when the priest
found his victim,

01:11:55.301 --> 01:11:57.468
"she was possessed by Calux.

01:11:57.470 --> 01:12:00.204
"She hid the priest's body
in the mission...

01:12:00.206 --> 01:12:02.074
"in pieces.

01:12:02.076 --> 01:12:04.946
"It took them a week
to find his head.

01:12:07.380 --> 01:12:10.115
"But Calux didn't want to stop.

01:12:10.117 --> 01:12:12.084
"He made us keep playing.

01:12:12.086 --> 01:12:13.988
Many of my sisters died."

01:12:16.090 --> 01:12:18.660
Wait, how did you
and the others escape?

01:12:32.739 --> 01:12:35.473
"The person
who released the demon

01:12:35.475 --> 01:12:37.342
"can trap it
with a simple ritual,

01:12:37.344 --> 01:12:39.380
but only by his own hand."

01:12:43.884 --> 01:12:47.218
Uh, this is the spell?
Uh, it's in Spanish.

01:12:47.220 --> 01:12:49.987
OLIVIA: "The spell must be
repeated seven times

01:12:49.989 --> 01:12:53.361
"and a sacrifice must be placed
in a pot sealed with wax.

01:13:00.768 --> 01:13:03.968
"As long as the pot
stays sealed in the mission,

01:13:03.970 --> 01:13:08.942
the door we opened for Calux
will also be sealed."

01:13:11.044 --> 01:13:13.480
Wait, I've seen
that pot before.

01:13:17.483 --> 01:13:19.284
Yeah. Look.

01:13:19.286 --> 01:13:21.285
But when I saw it,
it was broken

01:13:21.287 --> 01:13:24.054
and there was something inside
it and it smelled rotten.

01:13:24.056 --> 01:13:25.156
(INEZ GASPS)

01:13:25.158 --> 01:13:27.761
(INEZ GRUNTING FRANTICALLY)

01:13:46.513 --> 01:13:50.115
"Whoever broke the pot
will have to do the same."

01:13:50.117 --> 01:13:52.350
What was it?
The sacrifice.

01:13:52.352 --> 01:13:54.855
(INEZ GRUNTS)

01:13:56.290 --> 01:13:58.426
(INEZ WHIMPERING SOFTLY,
PANTING)

01:14:03.897 --> 01:14:06.334
It was you
who summoned the demon?

01:14:08.301 --> 01:14:09.402
(GASPING)

01:14:14.207 --> 01:14:16.143
♪ ♪

01:14:31.123 --> 01:14:34.058
BRAD: It's been a few years
since AP Spanish,

01:14:34.060 --> 01:14:37.462
but I think it says,
"I have called upon an evil.

01:14:37.464 --> 01:14:41.566
Silence my voice,
so the evil is no more."

01:14:41.568 --> 01:14:44.134
So when Carter and his friends
broke the pot at the mission...

01:14:44.136 --> 01:14:45.070
The demon was freed

01:14:45.072 --> 01:14:46.605
and possessed their game
of Truth or Dare.

01:14:46.607 --> 01:14:48.606
And we have to find
whoever broke that pot.

01:14:48.608 --> 01:14:50.976
But Giselle said somebody
named Sam trashed the place.

01:14:50.978 --> 01:14:53.244
And we have no idea who Sam is.

01:14:53.246 --> 01:14:56.481
- Or if he's even still alive.
- And if we do find him...

01:14:56.483 --> 01:14:58.048
What?

01:14:58.050 --> 01:15:00.285
"Hi, Sam. Do you mind
cutting out your tongue

01:15:00.287 --> 01:15:03.157
and sealing it in this
lovely handmade pot?"

01:15:04.892 --> 01:15:06.324
I'll check
Giselle's Facebook again,

01:15:06.326 --> 01:15:08.062
see if there's a Sam tagged.

01:15:09.295 --> 01:15:10.561
Still nothing from Markie?

01:15:10.563 --> 01:15:13.397
She's ignoring all my texts.

01:15:13.399 --> 01:15:14.665
Her turn's next.

01:15:14.667 --> 01:15:16.368
I'm gonna try
calling her again.

01:15:16.370 --> 01:15:18.570
(KNOCK ON DOOR)

01:15:18.572 --> 01:15:21.138
CHANG:
Brad? Brad!

01:15:21.140 --> 01:15:23.008
- (BRAD SIGHS)
- It's your father.

01:15:23.010 --> 01:15:26.378
Since Penelope, he's been...

01:15:26.380 --> 01:15:27.614
I'll get rid of him.

01:15:34.921 --> 01:15:36.857
Let's talk outside.

01:15:40.227 --> 01:15:42.296
(DOOR CLOSES)

01:15:46.198 --> 01:15:47.699
OFFICER:
I'm gonna grab coffee.

01:15:47.701 --> 01:15:49.066
(INDISTINCT
POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

01:15:49.068 --> 01:15:51.102
Look, uh, I'm hearing
some things

01:15:51.104 --> 01:15:53.103
about your, uh,
friend's murder.

01:15:53.105 --> 01:15:56.274
Kranis in Homicide isn't
convinced it's so simple.

01:15:56.276 --> 01:16:00.244
I know I don't need
to ask this, but...

01:16:00.246 --> 01:16:02.246
is there something
you're not telling us?

01:16:02.248 --> 01:16:03.647
No, I-I promise.

01:16:03.649 --> 01:16:05.417
Everything we told you
was true.

01:16:05.419 --> 01:16:08.719
(PHONE BUZZING)

01:16:08.721 --> 01:16:11.455
Markie, thank God.

01:16:11.457 --> 01:16:12.990
Why are you telling me
all this?

01:16:12.992 --> 01:16:14.392
'Cause I know Kranis is wrong,

01:16:14.394 --> 01:16:16.328
and I want you to know
what's going on.

01:16:16.330 --> 01:16:17.561
Look, you don't have to worry.

01:16:17.563 --> 01:16:20.133
I'm not gonna let
anything happen to you.

01:16:21.401 --> 01:16:23.504
You're still my son, Brad.

01:16:26.372 --> 01:16:28.308
(RADIO STATIC CRACKLES, HUMS)

01:16:30.376 --> 01:16:33.477
- You gonna get that?
- Get what?

01:16:33.479 --> 01:16:36.981
(DEMONIC VOICE, OVER RADIO):
Truth or dare, Brad?

01:16:36.983 --> 01:16:38.717
MARKIE: Yeah, I guess
I just needed some time alone.

01:16:38.719 --> 01:16:40.051
No, no, no.
It's-it's fine.

01:16:40.053 --> 01:16:41.453
Just get here
as fast as you can.

01:16:41.455 --> 01:16:43.454
And please be careful.
Your turn's next.

01:16:43.456 --> 01:16:46.324
I had my turn.
I chose truth.

01:16:46.326 --> 01:16:48.392
So did Lucas.

01:16:48.394 --> 01:16:51.362
And if the both of you
picked truth...

01:16:51.364 --> 01:16:53.365
CALUX (OVER RADIO):
You only have one choice.

01:16:53.367 --> 01:16:55.033
You sure there's nothing
you need to tell me?

01:16:55.035 --> 01:16:57.735
CALUX:
I dare you to steal his gun

01:16:57.737 --> 01:17:00.739
- and make him beg for his life.
- (STATIC CRACKLES)

01:17:00.741 --> 01:17:02.374
CHANG:
Son?

01:17:02.376 --> 01:17:06.710
Thank you, Dad, for everything.

01:17:06.712 --> 01:17:10.347
It's just, uh, there's just
one more thing I need to do,

01:17:10.349 --> 01:17:12.217
and I hope you can forgive me.

01:17:12.219 --> 01:17:15.219
Yeah. Yeah, yeah.
Of course.

01:17:15.221 --> 01:17:16.724
For what?

01:17:22.795 --> 01:17:25.065
It's okay.

01:17:28.068 --> 01:17:30.468
I need you to beg.
For your life.

01:17:30.470 --> 01:17:32.603
- The hell are you doing?
- BRAD: Beg for your life!

01:17:32.605 --> 01:17:34.772
CHANG:
Brad, please, put the gun down!

01:17:34.774 --> 01:17:36.775
- Just do as I say or I'll die.
- You don't have to do this!

01:17:36.777 --> 01:17:39.343
- Get on your knees.
- We have to go. Now!

01:17:39.345 --> 01:17:41.212
Do as I say.
I'll explain everything, okay?

01:17:41.214 --> 01:17:42.446
- I know I've been hard on you.
- Listen. No!

01:17:42.448 --> 01:17:43.448
- And I'm sorry.
- No.

01:17:43.450 --> 01:17:44.585
That's not what this is about.

01:17:50.357 --> 01:17:52.457
Beg! Please.
I'll explain everything.

01:17:52.459 --> 01:17:54.225
- Just beg.
- I guess you think I deserve this.

01:17:54.227 --> 01:17:55.759
No. No.

01:17:55.761 --> 01:17:57.430
Just, just, just, just beg!

01:18:02.102 --> 01:18:04.201
Please! Just beg
and I'll put down the gun.

01:18:04.203 --> 01:18:05.637
- What's that gonna prove, Brad?
- Just beg,

01:18:05.639 --> 01:18:08.109
- and I'll put down the gun! Beg!
- (GUNSHOT)

01:18:11.377 --> 01:18:13.143
No, no, no, no!

01:18:13.145 --> 01:18:15.512
- No! No!
- OLIVIA: Brad!

01:18:15.514 --> 01:18:17.615
Brad! No, no, no! No!

01:18:17.617 --> 01:18:18.783
OLIVIA:
No! No!

01:18:18.785 --> 01:18:20.587
Get a paramedic!

01:18:21.587 --> 01:18:23.387
Come on.

01:18:23.389 --> 01:18:24.755
Brad, Brad! No, no, no.

01:18:24.757 --> 01:18:26.557
Stay here.
You're gonna be fine.

01:18:26.559 --> 01:18:28.660
No! No!

01:18:28.662 --> 01:18:30.765
I need a paramedic! Help!

01:18:32.099 --> 01:18:34.468
I need a paramedic! Brad!

01:18:37.604 --> 01:18:39.838
(EXHALES)

01:18:39.840 --> 01:18:41.776
I'm so sorry.

01:18:43.609 --> 01:18:45.545
♪ ♪

01:18:50.750 --> 01:18:53.685
Guys, can we get out of here?

01:18:53.687 --> 01:18:55.820
I still need to talk
to the detective.

01:18:55.822 --> 01:18:57.588
I shouldn't have picked truth.

01:18:57.590 --> 01:18:59.257
LUCAS:
No, it's not your fault.

01:18:59.259 --> 01:19:01.392
I picked truth, too.

01:19:01.394 --> 01:19:03.594
We shouldn't have
left Brad alone.

01:19:03.596 --> 01:19:05.730
No, it wouldn't have mattered.

01:19:05.732 --> 01:19:07.565
This game is smart.
It's too smart.

01:19:07.567 --> 01:19:09.566
We're not playing it;
it's playing us.

01:19:09.568 --> 01:19:11.401
And none of this
is a coincidence.

01:19:11.403 --> 01:19:13.204
It waits for our most
vulnerable moments,

01:19:13.206 --> 01:19:15.539
and that's when it asks us.

01:19:15.541 --> 01:19:18.442
(DISTORTED): Yeah,
you got that right, Olivia.

01:19:18.444 --> 01:19:20.380
And now it's your turn.

01:19:21.648 --> 01:19:24.218
Truth or dare?

01:19:26.886 --> 01:19:29.286
What?

01:19:29.288 --> 01:19:30.657
What is it?

01:19:32.591 --> 01:19:34.859
Lucas just asked me.

01:19:34.861 --> 01:19:36.628
No, I didn't.

01:19:36.630 --> 01:19:37.765
(DISTORTED):
Truth or dare, Olivia?

01:19:39.398 --> 01:19:42.667
O-Okay.
Okay, you have to pick truth.

01:19:42.669 --> 01:19:45.203
Olivia, do it.

01:19:45.205 --> 01:19:46.637
- Dare.
- Olivia!

01:19:46.639 --> 01:19:49.740
I dare you...

01:19:49.742 --> 01:19:52.312
to tell Markie
the secret you fear most.

01:19:54.781 --> 01:19:57.484
What? Wh-What is it
making you do?

01:20:00.586 --> 01:20:03.491
Markie, there's something
important I need to tell you.

01:20:08.394 --> 01:20:10.196
(WHISPERS):
What?

01:20:12.898 --> 01:20:15.533
I was there
the night your dad died.

01:20:15.535 --> 01:20:18.602
I know what happened.

01:20:18.604 --> 01:20:20.471
What?

01:20:20.473 --> 01:20:22.707
What are you talking about?

01:20:22.709 --> 01:20:25.410
I had gotten into a fight
with my parents,

01:20:25.412 --> 01:20:27.779
so I went to your house.

01:20:27.781 --> 01:20:31.382
You weren't there,
so your dad let me in.

01:20:31.384 --> 01:20:34.985
He... he was drinking,
and he offered me one,

01:20:34.987 --> 01:20:36.620
so I took it.

01:20:36.622 --> 01:20:38.690
We had a few,
and then he told me

01:20:38.692 --> 01:20:40.924
that he had been fired
that day, 'cause he was,

01:20:40.926 --> 01:20:43.561
he was drinking on the job,
and I just,

01:20:43.563 --> 01:20:46.231
I felt really bad for him.
(SNIFFLES)

01:20:46.233 --> 01:20:49.234
But I told him that you and I

01:20:49.236 --> 01:20:51.305
would help him
figure things out.

01:20:56.576 --> 01:20:58.642
And then he called me
beautiful.

01:20:58.644 --> 01:21:02.746
And... I was drunk,
and I didn't know what to do,

01:21:02.748 --> 01:21:04.816
and then he leaned in
to kiss me,

01:21:04.818 --> 01:21:06.316
and I-I tried to push him off.

01:21:06.318 --> 01:21:07.819
I didn't do it, but he...

01:21:07.821 --> 01:21:10.420
(SNIFFLES)
he kept coming back stronger.

01:21:10.422 --> 01:21:13.527
But finally, I-I got free.

01:21:17.863 --> 01:21:20.464
He begged me to forgive him,

01:21:20.466 --> 01:21:22.667
said that he needed help,
but I was so scared,

01:21:22.669 --> 01:21:24.668
and I was confused,

01:21:24.670 --> 01:21:26.670
and I threatened
to tell you what happened,

01:21:26.672 --> 01:21:28.776
but he said that he would die
if you ever found out.

01:21:32.479 --> 01:21:35.849
I-I told him that you'd be
better off if he were dead.

01:21:38.518 --> 01:21:41.451
Markie, I am so sorry.

01:21:41.453 --> 01:21:45.289
I wanted to tell you, but
by the time I got ahold of you,

01:21:45.291 --> 01:21:47.825
he had already done it,
and you were devastated.

01:21:47.827 --> 01:21:50.061
It broke my heart.
I didn't know what to do.

01:21:50.063 --> 01:21:52.062
- Trust me, I..
- No.

01:21:52.064 --> 01:21:53.765
No, I'll never trust you again.

01:21:53.767 --> 01:21:56.700
- Markie...
- Don't!

01:21:56.702 --> 01:21:58.404
Don't.

01:21:59.805 --> 01:22:01.972
KRANIS:
Miss Barron.

01:22:01.974 --> 01:22:03.740
You're up.

01:22:03.742 --> 01:22:06.710
<i>"I know the game</i>

01:22:06.712 --> 01:22:08.812
"dared you
to set that woman on fire.

01:22:08.814 --> 01:22:10.647
"Tell me where to meet you,

01:22:10.649 --> 01:22:12.650
"or I'll wait outside
your family's house

01:22:12.652 --> 01:22:15.852
until the game dares me
to do the same to them."

01:22:15.854 --> 01:22:18.923
That is... quite a threat.

01:22:18.925 --> 01:22:21.459
We traced the I.P.
to your laptop.

01:22:21.461 --> 01:22:23.460
I-I know that that...

01:22:23.462 --> 01:22:25.429
looks bad, but I...

01:22:25.431 --> 01:22:27.432
I just needed
to get her attention.

01:22:27.434 --> 01:22:28.999
Yeah, I know
you're playing some kind

01:22:29.001 --> 01:22:30.868
of Truth or Dare game,
but what I don't understand is:

01:22:30.870 --> 01:22:32.003
why are people dying?

01:22:32.005 --> 01:22:33.838
There's only four of you left.

01:22:33.840 --> 01:22:37.075
- I'd like to keep the rest of you guys alive.
- Four?

01:22:37.077 --> 01:22:38.709
Everyone who's dead
was in Mexico.

01:22:38.711 --> 01:22:40.610
That leaves you,
Markie and Lucas,

01:22:40.612 --> 01:22:42.315
and Giselle's friend,
Sam Meehan.

01:22:43.716 --> 01:22:45.516
Sam?

01:22:45.518 --> 01:22:47.485
Wait, he's alive?

01:22:47.487 --> 01:22:48.956
You know him?

01:22:53.526 --> 01:22:55.426
No.

01:22:55.428 --> 01:22:58.529
No, that-that's just someone
that Giselle had mentioned.

01:22:58.531 --> 01:23:00.530
Ah. He's holed up
in an apartment.

01:23:00.532 --> 01:23:02.834
Won't talk to anybody.
Said I had to arrest him

01:23:02.836 --> 01:23:04.936
if I wanted to speak
to him again.

01:23:04.938 --> 01:23:07.672
Olivia, what the hell
is happening here?

01:23:07.674 --> 01:23:09.906
Could I get some water, please?

01:23:09.908 --> 01:23:11.542
(SIGHS)

01:23:11.544 --> 01:23:13.479
(QUIETLY):
Thanks.

01:23:18.818 --> 01:23:20.752
KRANIS: Marcus, I'm gonna
need a glass of water.

01:23:20.754 --> 01:23:22.488
- (CAMERA CLICKS)
- MARCUS: Yes, sir, right away.

01:23:26.425 --> 01:23:28.125
Am I being charged?

01:23:28.127 --> 01:23:30.460
Not yet.

01:23:30.462 --> 01:23:32.733
Okay, then I need to go.

01:23:39.671 --> 01:23:42.041
♪ ♪

01:24:01.961 --> 01:24:04.064
♪ ♪

01:24:21.547 --> 01:24:23.213
(DOOR BUZZES)

01:24:23.215 --> 01:24:24.915
Carter is Sam.

01:24:24.917 --> 01:24:26.950
He was using a fake name.

01:24:26.952 --> 01:24:28.985
But Giselle acted like
they were different people?

01:24:28.987 --> 01:24:31.054
Well, she was probably
trying to protect him,

01:24:31.056 --> 01:24:34.158
but she slipped up and she
used his real name. Come on.

01:24:34.160 --> 01:24:36.095
♪ ♪

01:24:57.684 --> 01:24:59.683
(BREATH TREMBLING)

01:24:59.685 --> 01:25:01.621
♪ ♪

01:25:09.095 --> 01:25:11.632
(TIRES SCREECH)

01:25:18.938 --> 01:25:21.675
Markie? Markie!

01:25:25.010 --> 01:25:26.647
Markie?

01:25:31.017 --> 01:25:32.717
(DOORKNOB RATTLES)

01:25:32.719 --> 01:25:35.151
Markie, please open the door.
We need to talk.

01:25:35.153 --> 01:25:36.889
(DOORKNOB RATTLES)

01:25:41.126 --> 01:25:43.694
What are you doing?

01:25:43.696 --> 01:25:45.795
What my father did.

01:25:45.797 --> 01:25:48.231
- Markie, please put it down.
- (CRYING)

01:25:48.233 --> 01:25:51.035
Why?

01:25:51.037 --> 01:25:52.802
I don't have anything.

01:25:52.804 --> 01:25:55.039
You have me.

01:25:55.041 --> 01:25:58.042
No. (SNIFFLES)

01:25:58.044 --> 01:26:00.544
- Now the game has us.
- (GUN COCKS)

01:26:00.546 --> 01:26:04.248
I hid the truth about your dad
to protect you.

01:26:04.250 --> 01:26:07.250
But I was wrong.

01:26:07.252 --> 01:26:09.085
Every single day,

01:26:09.087 --> 01:26:11.757
I wish I could take back
what I said to him.

01:26:13.826 --> 01:26:16.063
And he tried before.

01:26:18.264 --> 01:26:22.066
It's not your fault.

01:26:22.068 --> 01:26:24.067
(BREATH TREMBLING)

01:26:24.069 --> 01:26:27.905
We can't change the past.

01:26:27.907 --> 01:26:29.906
But we can still have a future.

01:26:29.908 --> 01:26:31.909
We can end this game.

01:26:31.911 --> 01:26:34.078
How?

01:26:34.080 --> 01:26:36.517
Carter... I know where he is.

01:26:38.785 --> 01:26:40.720
(SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE)

01:26:43.790 --> 01:26:45.725
♪ ♪

01:26:53.232 --> 01:26:54.899
Okay, so what's the plan?

01:26:54.901 --> 01:26:57.834
- We just have to get him back to the mission.
- Okay.

01:26:57.836 --> 01:27:01.071
So don't open with "We need you
to cut out your own tongue"?

01:27:01.073 --> 01:27:04.874
- Here it is. Six.
- (KNOCKING)

01:27:04.876 --> 01:27:08.044
SAM: Go away!
I don't want to talk to anyone!

01:27:08.046 --> 01:27:09.981
LUCAS:
Screw this.

01:27:09.983 --> 01:27:11.182
You...

01:27:11.184 --> 01:27:12.383
- Wait, wait, wait!
- OLIVIA: Carter!

01:27:12.385 --> 01:27:14.051
Or is it Sam?

01:27:14.053 --> 01:27:16.119
- How did you find me?
- We were motivated.

01:27:16.121 --> 01:27:18.155
- What the hell happened in here?
- The game.

01:27:18.157 --> 01:27:21.825
No contact with the outside.
Nothing in here can hurt me.

01:27:21.827 --> 01:27:25.228
- This is your plan?
- My plan is to wait it out.

01:27:25.230 --> 01:27:26.731
No, that was your second plan.

01:27:26.733 --> 01:27:28.199
Your first plan
was to screw us.

01:27:28.201 --> 01:27:31.768
Three of my best friends
are dead because of you!

01:27:31.770 --> 01:27:34.070
I'm sorry.
I lost friends, too, okay?

01:27:34.072 --> 01:27:36.140
If I could take it all back,
I would.

01:27:36.142 --> 01:27:37.642
There is a way.

01:27:37.644 --> 01:27:40.043
But we all have to go back
to the mission.

01:27:40.045 --> 01:27:42.213
A way to what?
To what, end the game? How?

01:27:42.215 --> 01:27:45.953
Just... trust me.
We have to go back.

01:27:49.022 --> 01:27:52.255
Uh-uh. No, this is
another dare, right?

01:27:52.257 --> 01:27:55.058
- The game's daring you to lure me out? Is that...
- No.

01:27:55.060 --> 01:27:57.395
She's telling the truth.

01:27:57.397 --> 01:27:59.730
And why should I trust you?

01:27:59.732 --> 01:28:01.899
Because we want
the same thing.

01:28:01.901 --> 01:28:03.303
We want to survive.

01:28:05.337 --> 01:28:07.338
Look...

01:28:07.340 --> 01:28:10.274
I'm gonna tell you what you
should've told me at the bar.

01:28:10.276 --> 01:28:12.144
Piss off.

01:28:19.152 --> 01:28:22.085
Okay, sweet little Olivia's
not shooting anyone.

01:28:22.087 --> 01:28:25.257
Try me. I dare you.

01:28:33.232 --> 01:28:35.132
- LUCAS: Come on, let's go.
- SAM: I am moving.

01:28:35.134 --> 01:28:38.069
MARKIE:
Right through here.

01:28:38.071 --> 01:28:40.006
OLIVIA:
Go.

01:28:43.309 --> 01:28:45.245
♪ ♪

01:28:53.419 --> 01:28:55.886
SAM: Is this ritual
that old nun told you about

01:28:55.888 --> 01:28:57.288
actually gonna work?

01:28:57.290 --> 01:28:59.660
OLIVIA: There's only one way
to find out.

01:29:06.431 --> 01:29:08.065
(SAM LAUGHS)

01:29:08.067 --> 01:29:11.235
So we're gonna end this
with a séance?

01:29:11.237 --> 01:29:14.003
We are not ending it.
You are.

01:29:14.005 --> 01:29:16.440
Me? I tried.

01:29:16.442 --> 01:29:18.812
We all know how that
turned out. (CHUCKLES)

01:29:20.246 --> 01:29:22.114
(GRUNTS, GASPS)

01:29:23.315 --> 01:29:25.452
- Stay down.
- (COUGHING)

01:29:27.053 --> 01:29:29.520
Here. Take this. Take it!

01:29:29.522 --> 01:29:31.358
Say it seven times.

01:29:32.825 --> 01:29:34.760
(SAM PANTING)

01:29:37.063 --> 01:29:39.295
What are you
gonna do with that?

01:29:39.297 --> 01:29:42.169
I'm giving it to you.

01:29:43.269 --> 01:29:45.369
Take it. Now!

01:29:45.371 --> 01:29:48.405
Now say the words seven times.

01:29:48.407 --> 01:29:49.807
Go!

01:29:49.809 --> 01:29:51.040
Uh...

01:29:51.042 --> 01:29:53.377
<i>"Hermaro almas..."</i>

01:29:53.379 --> 01:29:55.881
(RUMBLING)

01:29:58.151 --> 01:30:00.851
- Did you feel that?
- OLIVIA: Don't stop.

01:30:00.853 --> 01:30:03.219
- Just-just tell me what's going on!
- Keep going!

01:30:03.221 --> 01:30:06.156
SAM:
All right... (STAMMERS)

01:30:06.158 --> 01:30:09.093
<i>"...silencia mi voz para que
el mal no sea más.</i>

01:30:09.095 --> 01:30:11.294
(RUMBLING)

01:30:11.296 --> 01:30:13.496
Say it again.

01:30:13.498 --> 01:30:14.698
<i>"Hermaro almas,</i>

01:30:14.700 --> 01:30:18.134
<i>silencia mi voz para que
el mal no sea más."</i>

01:30:18.136 --> 01:30:19.503
(LOUD BOOM, RUMBLING)

01:30:19.505 --> 01:30:21.571
(GASPING)

01:30:21.573 --> 01:30:23.406
Five more times.

01:30:23.408 --> 01:30:25.308
<i>"Hermaro almas,
silencia mi voz</i>

01:30:25.310 --> 01:30:27.214
<i>para que el mal no sea más."</i>

01:30:29.314 --> 01:30:31.315
(DISTORTED):
Truth or dare, Lucas?

01:30:31.317 --> 01:30:33.420
(SAM CONTINUES RECITING
IN SPANISH)

01:30:35.520 --> 01:30:38.121
Dare.

01:30:38.123 --> 01:30:40.356
(DISTORTED CHUCKLING)

01:30:40.358 --> 01:30:42.826
<i>"Hermaro almas,
silencia mi voz</i>

01:30:42.828 --> 01:30:44.829
<i>mi voz para que el mal no..."</i>

01:30:44.831 --> 01:30:47.130
- Where are you going?
- Just got to get away from here.

01:30:47.132 --> 01:30:49.200
Wait, wait, wait.
You can't go.

01:30:49.202 --> 01:30:50.567
Your turn's next.

01:30:50.569 --> 01:30:53.337
- (GASPING)
- I just had my turn.

01:30:53.339 --> 01:30:55.873
- Got to get away from you both.
- Why?

01:30:55.875 --> 01:30:57.575
Because it dared me to choose.

01:30:57.577 --> 01:30:59.043
You already have.
You love Markie.

01:30:59.045 --> 01:31:01.014
Choose which one of you
to kill.

01:31:06.352 --> 01:31:07.450
Luke.

01:31:07.452 --> 01:31:09.453
What, so he's just leaving?!

01:31:09.455 --> 01:31:11.187
Don't stop.
Two more times.

01:31:11.189 --> 01:31:12.623
<i>"Hermaro almas,</i>

01:31:12.625 --> 01:31:15.426
<i>silencia mi voz para que
el mal no sea más."</i>

01:31:15.428 --> 01:31:16.893
Luke?

01:31:16.895 --> 01:31:19.562
Luke? Why did you pick dare?

01:31:19.564 --> 01:31:22.199
Because I knew if I didn't,
then one of you would have to.

01:31:22.201 --> 01:31:24.267
And we're so close.

01:31:24.269 --> 01:31:26.203
And I won't let
the game kill you.

01:31:26.205 --> 01:31:29.272
(CRYING):
You're such an idiot.

01:31:29.274 --> 01:31:32.008
What can I say?

01:31:32.010 --> 01:31:34.011
You do that to me.

01:31:34.013 --> 01:31:35.948
♪ ♪

01:31:46.224 --> 01:31:51.094
<i>"Hermaro almas, silencia mi voz
para que el mal no sea más."</i>

01:31:51.096 --> 01:31:53.897
(LOUD BOOM, CLATTERING)

01:31:53.899 --> 01:31:55.531
That's seven.

01:31:55.533 --> 01:31:57.534
We got to get out of here.
This place is coming down.

01:31:57.536 --> 01:31:59.069
No, there's one more thing
to do.

01:31:59.071 --> 01:32:01.237
Pick up the knife.

01:32:01.239 --> 01:32:03.042
I can't do it for you.

01:32:04.609 --> 01:32:06.513
Pick it up!

01:32:09.014 --> 01:32:10.481
And do what?

01:32:10.483 --> 01:32:12.682
I'm so sorry, Sam.

01:32:12.684 --> 01:32:14.584
But you unleashed this evil,

01:32:14.586 --> 01:32:17.687
which means you're the only one
who can stop it.

01:32:17.689 --> 01:32:19.690
(PANTING)

01:32:19.692 --> 01:32:22.159
I need you to cut out
your tongue.

01:32:22.161 --> 01:32:24.695
N-No, that's insane.

01:32:24.697 --> 01:32:26.696
Please!
It's the only way we survive!

01:32:26.698 --> 01:32:28.535
(LOUD BOOM, CLATTERING)

01:32:30.635 --> 01:32:32.104
(OLIVIA GASPS)

01:32:34.607 --> 01:32:36.573
You take care of each other.

01:32:36.575 --> 01:32:39.479
No. (CRYING)

01:32:48.420 --> 01:32:50.256
(GASPS)

01:32:53.591 --> 01:32:55.895
- No. No.
- OLIVIA: Do it.

01:33:00.332 --> 01:33:02.132
- Lucas, stop!
- That's not Lucas.

01:33:02.134 --> 01:33:04.401
Do it now, Carter.

01:33:04.403 --> 01:33:07.137
- Before it's too late!
- (WALL CRACKLING)

01:33:07.139 --> 01:33:08.371
Don't you want to live?!

01:33:08.373 --> 01:33:11.508
You do not have a choice!
Do it!

01:33:11.510 --> 01:33:14.648
I can't believe
I'm about to do this.

01:33:17.450 --> 01:33:19.685
(LUCAS SCREAMING)

01:33:21.987 --> 01:33:23.654
(DISTORTED): I will murder
everyone you've ever known!

01:33:23.656 --> 01:33:26.190
No, they are not in this!
It's just us!

01:33:26.192 --> 01:33:28.592
You're right.

01:33:28.594 --> 01:33:31.527
But Lucas is,
and he didn't do his dare.

01:33:31.529 --> 01:33:33.163
So now he dies.

01:33:33.165 --> 01:33:34.935
- (GRUNTS)
- (OLIVIA AND MARKIE GASP)

01:33:37.769 --> 01:33:39.672
(GRUNTING)

01:33:44.109 --> 01:33:46.412
(KNIFE STABS)

01:33:57.790 --> 01:33:59.125
No!

01:34:06.732 --> 01:34:08.635
(CRYING QUIETLY)

01:34:21.279 --> 01:34:24.181
Lucas refused his dare
to save us.

01:34:24.183 --> 01:34:25.582
(SHALLOW PANTING)

01:34:25.584 --> 01:34:28.185
We have to finish this.

01:34:28.187 --> 01:34:30.654
Calux killed Carter.
The spell won't work.

01:34:30.656 --> 01:34:34.792
No, we lost the second
we started this game.

01:34:34.794 --> 01:34:39.329
The second we came here.

01:34:39.331 --> 01:34:41.432
Carter was dared
to bring us here,

01:34:41.434 --> 01:34:44.634
because this is where you can
add new people to the game.

01:34:44.636 --> 01:34:46.436
I have an idea.
Your turn's next.

01:34:46.438 --> 01:34:48.672
When you're asked,
I need you to pick dare.

01:34:48.674 --> 01:34:50.673
Why would I do that?

01:34:50.675 --> 01:34:54.113
(DISTORTED, SINGSONGY):
Markie...

01:34:55.214 --> 01:34:56.746
Truth or dare?

01:34:56.748 --> 01:34:59.516
(CRYING):
Now Lucas is asking me.

01:34:59.518 --> 01:35:01.517
Pick dare.

01:35:01.519 --> 01:35:04.221
- But don't do it.
- What? I'll die.

01:35:04.223 --> 01:35:06.255
Markie, I am so sorry

01:35:06.257 --> 01:35:08.659
for keeping that secret
from you for so long.

01:35:08.661 --> 01:35:10.393
And I swear to you

01:35:10.395 --> 01:35:12.396
I will never, ever keep
anything from you again.

01:35:12.398 --> 01:35:14.798
But we survive this
only if we trust each other.

01:35:14.800 --> 01:35:16.169
Okay?

01:35:18.737 --> 01:35:21.237
- Okay.
- Trust me.

01:35:21.239 --> 01:35:23.240
CALUX:
You have to pick.

01:35:23.242 --> 01:35:24.874
Dare.

01:35:24.876 --> 01:35:27.777
I dare you to shoot Olivia.

01:35:27.779 --> 01:35:31.347
He wants me to shoot you.

01:35:31.349 --> 01:35:33.150
You got to trust me, Markie.
Don't do it.

01:35:33.152 --> 01:35:35.218
This is the only way
to save us both.

01:35:35.220 --> 01:35:38.123
Okay. I trust you.

01:35:41.227 --> 01:35:43.162
I won't do it.

01:35:48.666 --> 01:35:50.267
No!

01:35:50.269 --> 01:35:51.368
(GROANS)

01:35:51.370 --> 01:35:53.570
(OLIVIA PANTING)

01:35:53.572 --> 01:35:55.438
Dare complete, Calux.

01:35:55.440 --> 01:35:57.141
Your turn.

01:35:57.143 --> 01:35:59.910
Truth or dare?

01:35:59.912 --> 01:36:01.477
(DISTORTED):
I'm not in this game.

01:36:01.479 --> 01:36:03.146
No, once you're asked,
you're in.

01:36:03.148 --> 01:36:04.780
Those are the rules, right?

01:36:04.782 --> 01:36:06.682
So, truth or dare, asshole?

01:36:06.684 --> 01:36:09.418
Truth.

01:36:09.420 --> 01:36:13.323
How do we get out
of this game alive?

01:36:13.325 --> 01:36:15.424
(CHUCKLES)

01:36:15.426 --> 01:36:17.527
You can't.

01:36:17.529 --> 01:36:20.364
Carter was the only one
who could stop this.

01:36:20.366 --> 01:36:24.368
So now the game won't end
until all the players are dead.

01:36:24.370 --> 01:36:26.770
And your turn's next.

01:36:26.772 --> 01:36:31.508
Unless you find
some new friends to play with.

01:36:31.510 --> 01:36:34.581
But that's not
gonna happen, is it?

01:36:38.483 --> 01:36:41.384
- Your arm.
- I'm okay.

01:36:41.386 --> 01:36:43.253
Well, did it work?

01:36:43.255 --> 01:36:45.755
It's not over. (PANTING)

01:36:45.757 --> 01:36:48.758
The game will never end,
not as long as we're alive.

01:36:48.760 --> 01:36:50.259
(GRUNTS)

01:36:50.261 --> 01:36:52.862
What are you doing?

01:36:52.864 --> 01:36:55.167
I'm choosing you.

01:37:03.908 --> 01:37:05.844
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:37:08.947 --> 01:37:11.582
OLIVIA: <i>My friends and I
went on a trip to Mexico</i>

01:37:11.584 --> 01:37:14.618
